ates]]\n[[Category:Violence against LGBT people in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mass shooting at gay nightclub in Orlando, Florida, U.S.}} \n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use American English|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title       = Pulse nightclub shooting\n| partof      = [[Terrorism in the United States]]\n| image       = 1912 S Orange Ave 2.png\n| alt         = A street-level view of a small white structure with a blue roof, black awnings, and empty parking lot\n| caption     = The [[Pulse nightclub]] in 2006. It had been painted black by the time of the shooting.\n| map         = {{Location map | USA Florida\n| width       = 250\n| label       = Orlando\n| position    = centre\n| background  =\n| coordinates = {{coord|28.51961|-81.37683}}\n}}\n{{-}}\n {{OSM Location map\n |coord={{Coord|28.51961|-81.37683}}\n |float=center |zoom=16\n |width=300\n |height=220\n |scalemark=40\n |mark-coord1 = {{Coord|28.51961|-81.37683}}\n |shape1=n-square <!--any way to use the same squircle?-->\n |shape-color1=\n |shape-outline1=\n |mark-size1=\n |fullscreen-option=1\n }}\n| map_alt     =\n| map_caption =\n| location    = Pulse Nightclub<br>1912 S. Orange Avenue<br>[[Orlando, Florida]], U.S.\n| target      = Patrons of [[Pulse nightclub|Pulse]] nightclub\n| coordinates = {{coord|28.51961|-81.37683|region:US-FL_type:event|display=inline,title}}\n| date        = {{start date and age|2016|06|12|mf=y}}\n| time        = {{nowrap|2:02 a.m.&nbsp;\u2013 5:14 a.m.}} [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n| timezone    = [[UTC\u221204:00]]\n| type        = [[Mass shooting]], [[terrorist attack]], [[hostage-taking]]<!--Per [[Template:Infobox civilian attack]], \"type\" refers to the perpetrator's METHOD, not MOTIVE.-->\n| fatalities  = 50 (including the perpetrator)\n| injuries    = 58 (53 by gunfire)<ref name=\"auto000\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.policefoundation.org/publication/rescue-response-and-resilience-a-critical-incident-review-of-the-orlando-public-safety-response-to-the-attack-on-the-pulse-nightclub/|title=Rescue, Response, and Resilience|accessdate=March 11, 2020|via=www.policefoundation.org}}</ref>\n| perp        = [[Omar Mateen]]\n| motive      = <!--Wait until the Florida Department of Law Enforcement announces motive before adding, per Talk:2016 Orlando nightclub shooting#Are we consensual enough on the motive yet?.-->\n| weapons     = {{ubl | [[SIG MCX|Sig Sauer MCX]] [[semi-automatic rifle]] | [[Glock#Glock 17|Glock 17]] [[semi-automatic pistol]]}}\n| numparts    = <!-- or | numpart     = -->\n| dfens       = <!-- or | dfen        = -->\n| website     = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n}}<!--Citations are often omitted from the lead section of an article, insofar as the lead summarizes information for which sources are given later in the article, although quotations and controversial statements, particularly if about living persons, should be supported by citations even in the lead. See [[WP:LEADCITE]] for more information. Please add citations to the body.-->\n\nOn {{nowrap|June 12}}, 2016, [[Omar Mateen]], a 29-year-old [[security guard]], killed 49 people and wounded 53 others in a [[mass shooting]] inside [[Pulse nightclub|Pulse]], a [[gay bar|gay nightclub]] in [[Orlando, Florida]], United States. [[Orlando Police Department]] officers shot and killed him after a three-hour standoff.\n\nIn a [[9-1-1]] call made shortly after the shooting began, Mateen [[Bay'ah|swore allegiance]] to the leader of the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]], [[Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi]], and said the U.S. killing of [[Abu Waheeb]] in Iraq the previous month \"triggered\" the shooting. He later told a negotiator he was \"out here right now\" because of the American-led interventions [[American-led intervention in Iraq (2014\u2013present)|in Iraq]] and [[American-led intervention in Syria|in Syria]] and that the negotiator should tell the United States to stop the bombing. The incident was deemed a [[terrorist attack]] by [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] investigators.\n\nPulse was hosting a \"Latin Night\", and most of the victims were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic]]. It is the deadliest incident in the [[history of violence against LGBT people in the United States]] and the deadliest terrorist attack in the U.S. since the [[September 11 attacks]] in 2001. At the time, it was the deadliest [[mass shooting]] by a single gunman in U.S. history, being surpassed a year later by the [[2017 Las Vegas shooting|Las Vegas shooting]].\n\n==Shooting==\n===First shots and hostage situation===\nOn {{nowrap|June 11}}, 2016, Pulse, a [[gay bar|gay nightclub]] in Orlando, Florida, was hosting \"Latin Night\", a weekly Saturday night event drawing a primarily [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic]] crowd.<ref>{{cite news |last=Rothaus |first=Steve |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Pulse Orlando shooting scene a popular LGBT club where employees, patrons 'like family' |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/community/gay-south-florida/article83301677.html |work=The Miami Herald |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615082724/http://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/community/gay-south-florida/article83301677.html |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Tsukayama |first1=Hayley |last2=Berman |first2=Mark |last3=Markon |first3=Jerry |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Gunman who killed 49 in Orlando nightclub had pledged allegiance to ISIS |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-nation/wp/2016/06/12/orlando-nightclub-shooting-about-20-dead-in-domestic-terror-incident-at-gay-club/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615021024/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-nation/wp/2016/06/12/orlando-nightclub-shooting-about-20-dead-in-domestic-terror-incident-at-gay-club/ |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> About 320 people were inside the club, which was serving [[last call (bar term)|last call]] drinks at around {{nowrap|2:00 a.m.}} [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]] on {{nowrap|June 12}}.<ref name=\"abc39789552\" /><ref name=\"SantoraLastCall\">{{cite news |last=Santora |first=Marc |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Last Call at Pulse Nightclub, and Then Shots Rang Out |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/last-call-at-orlando-club-and-then-the-shots-rang-out.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612220954/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/last-call-at-orlando-club-and-then-the-shots-rang-out.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> At around the same time, Omar Mateen arrived at the club via rental van, parking it in the parking lot of a neighboring car shop.<ref name=\"auto000\" /><ref name=\"timeline tampabay\">{{cite news |author=<!--New York Times staff writer(s)?; no by-line.--> |title=A timeline of what happened at the Orlando nightclub shooting |url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/publicsafety/crime/a-timeline-of-what-happened-at-the-orlando-nightclub-shooting/2281363 |agency=The Tampa Bay Times |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613114415/http://www.tampabay.com/news/publicsafety/crime/a-timeline-of-what-happened-at-the-orlando-nightclub-shooting/2281363 |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> He got out and approached the building on foot, armed with a [[SIG Sauer]] [[SIG MCX|MCX]]<ref name=\"911CallSignificance\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Significance of Orlando gunman calling 911 during standoff |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-shooting-investigation-gunman-omar-mateen-911-call |publisher=CBS News |date=June 13, 2016 |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614075410/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-shooting-investigation-gunman-omar-mateen-911-call/ |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> [[semi-automatic rifle]] and a [[9\u00d719mm Parabellum|9mm]] [[Glock#Glock 17|Glock 17]] [[semi-automatic pistol]].<ref name=\"NPR AR15\">{{cite news |last=Zarroli |first=Jim |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Type Of Rifle Used In Orlando Is Popular With Hobbyists, Easy To Use |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/06/13/481877159/the-rifle-used-in-orlando-is-lightweight-easy-to-use-and-oh-so-deadly |publisher=NPR |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613234604/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/06/13/481877159/the-rifle-used-in-orlando-is-lightweight-easy-to-use-and-oh-so-deadly |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"NRB AR15\">{{cite news |first=Corky |last=Siemaszko |date=June 12, 2016 |title=AR-15 Style Rifle Used in Orlando Massacre Has Bloody Pedigree |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/ar-15-rifle-used-orlando-massacre-has-bloody-pedigree-n590581 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613230653/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/ar-15-rifle-used-orlando-massacre-has-bloody-pedigree-n590581 |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Time AR15\">{{cite news |last=Drabold |first=Will |date=June 13, 2016 |title=What to Know About the Gun Used in the Orlando Shooting |url=http://time.com/4366658/orlando-shooting-ar-15-gun-control/ |work=Time |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614042607/http://time.com/4366658/orlando-shooting-ar-15-gun-control/ |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"JansenUSAToday\">{{cite news |last=Jansen |first=Bart |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Weapons gunman used in Orlando shooting are high-capacity, common |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/06/14/guns-used-kill-49-orlando-high-capacity-common-weapons/85887260/ |work=USA Today |access-date=June 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618151610/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/06/14/guns-used-kill-49-orlando-high-capacity-common-weapons/85887260/ |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref> He was wearing a green, blue, and white plaid dress shirt, a white T-shirt underneath and tan cargo pants.<ref name=\"auto000\" /> At {{nowrap|2:02 a.m.}}, Mateen bypassed Officer Adam Gruler, a uniformed off-duty [[Orlando Police Department]] (OPD) officer working extra duty<ref name=\"TMZVideo\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Orlando Mass Shooting: Mateen Was About To Kill More ... Chief Describes Final Assault |url=http://m.tmz.com/#article/2016/06/13/orlando-mass-shooting-police-fbi-news-conference/ |work=TMZ |date=June 13, 2016 |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613025249/http://m.tmz.com/#article/2016/06/13/orlando-mass-shooting-police-fbi-news-conference/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref name=abcnews1>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/report-reveals-details-florida-nightclub-shooting-46794467 |title=Officer asked Pulse shooting victims: 'If you're alive, raise your hand' |work=ABC News |date=April 14, 2017 |accessdate=April 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414130216/http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/report-reveals-details-florida-nightclub-shooting-46794467 |archivedate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> as a security guard, entered the building through its southern entrance, and began shooting patrons.<ref name=\"auto000\" /><ref name=\"abc39789552\" /><ref name=\"SantoraLastCall\">{{cite news |last=Santora |first=Marc |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Last Call at Pulse Nightclub, and Then Shots Rang Out |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/last-call-at-orlando-club-and-then-the-shots-rang-out.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612220954/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/last-call-at-orlando-club-and-then-the-shots-rang-out.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"MozingoPearceWilkinson\" /> Dozens were killed or severely injured, either directly or by ricochets.<ref name=\"auto000\" /><ref name=orlandosentinel1>{{cite web |last1=Hayes |first1=Christal |last2=Harris |first2=David |last3=Lotan |first3=Gal Tziperman |last4=Doornbos |first4=Caitlin |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-presentation-orlando-police-20170412-story.html |title=Exclusive: New Pulse review from Orlando police reveals details, lessons learned |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=April 13, 2017 |accessdate=April 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413220820/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-presentation-orlando-police-20170412-story.html |archivedate=April 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nRealizing his service pistol would be no match against Mateen's rifle, Gruler took cover and called in a signal for assistance.<ref name=\"auto000\" /> When he witnessed Mateen shooting two patrons attempting to escape through an emergency exit, Gruler fired shots at him.<ref name=\"auto000\" /><ref name=\"NBC.Shooting\">{{cite news |last1=Grimson |first1=Matthew |last2=Wyllie |first2=David |last3=Fieldstadt |first3=Elisha |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Orlando Nightclub Shooting: Mass Casualties After Gunman Opens Fire in Gay Club |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/orlando-nightclub-shooting-emergency-services-respond-reports-gunman-n590446 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612141047/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/orlando-nightclub-shooting-emergency-services-respond-reports-gunman-n590446 |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"MozingoPearceWilkinson\">{{cite news |last1=Mozingo |first1=Joe |last2=Pearce |first2=Matt |last3=Wilkinson |first3=Tracy |date=June 13, 2016 |title='An act of terror and an act of hate': The aftermath of America's worst mass shooting |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/nationnow/la-na-orlando-nightclub-shooting-20160612-snap-story.html |work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612095327/http://www.latimes.com/nation/nationnow/la-na-orlando-nightclub-shooting-20160612-snap-story.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> In response, Mateen withdrew back into the nightclub and continued shooting victims as he traversed through the building, sometimes firing into bodies without checking whether they were alive or dead.<ref name=\"auto000\" /> When additional officers arrived at the nightclub beginning at 2:04&nbsp;a.m., Gruler shouted \"[The gunman]'s in the patio!\" and resumed firing at Mateen a minute later.<ref name=\"auto000\" /><ref name=abcnews1/><ref name=\"Orlando Sentinel Timeline\">{{cite web |last1=Gibson |first1=Andrew |title=Orlando nightclub shooting timeline: Four hours of terror unfold |url=https://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-pulse-nightclub-shooting-timeline-htmlstory.html |website=Orlando Sentinel |accessdate=February 16, 2019}}</ref> Two officers joined Gruler in engaging Mateen, who then retreated farther into the nightclub and \"began a 'hostage situation'\" in one of the bathrooms.<ref name=\"auto000\" /><ref name=\"abc39789552\">{{cite news |last1=Caplan |first1=David |last2=Hayden |first2=Michael Edison |date=June 12, 2016 |title=At Least 50 Dead in Orlando Gay Club Shooting, Suspect Pledged Allegiance to ISIS, Officials Say |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/multiple-injuries-shooting-orlando-nightclub-police/story?id=39789552 |publisher=ABC News |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612100306/http://abcnews.go.com/US/multiple-injuries-shooting-orlando-nightclub-police/story?id=39789552 |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=50 dead, Islamic terrorism tie eyed in Orlando gay bar shooting |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/pulse-nightclub-shooting-orlando/ |publisher=CBS News |agency=Associated Press |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612100037/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/pulse-nightclub-shooting-orlando/ |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"CNN.Timeline\" /> In less than five minutes, Mateen had fired approximately 200 rounds, pausing only to reload.<ref name=\"auto000\" />\n\nDuring the shooting, some of the people who were trapped inside the club sought help by calling or sending [[text messages]] to friends and relatives. Initially, some of them thought the gunshots were firecrackers or part of the music.<ref name=\"NYT.Visual\">{{cite news |last1=Aisch |first1=Gregor |last2=Buchanan |first2=Larry |last3=Burgess |first3=Joe |last4=Fessenden |first4=Ford |last5=Keller |first5=Josh |last6=Lai |first6=K.K. Rebecca |last7=Mykhyalyshyn |first7=Iaryna |last8=Park |first8=Haeyoun |last9=Pearce |first9=Adam |last10=Parshina-Kottas |first10=Yuliya |last11=Pe\u00e7anha |first11=Sergio |last12=Singhvi |first12=Anjali |last13=Watkins |first13=Derek |last14=Yourish |first14=Karen |date=June 12, 2016 |title=What Happened Inside the Orlando Nightclub |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2016/06/12/us/what-happened-at-the-orlando-nightclub-shooting.html |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612220932/http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2016/06/12/us/what-happened-at-the-orlando-nightclub-shooting.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"AlvarezAnguish\">{{cite news |last1=Alvarez |first1=Lizette |author-link1=Lizette Alvarez |last2=P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |first2=Richard |author-link2=Richard P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |last3=Hauser |first3=Christine |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Orlando Police Detail Battle to End Massacre at Gay Nightclub |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/14/us/orlando-shooting.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613140441/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/14/us/orlando-shooting.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"TeleLawlerAlexander\">{{cite news |last1=Alexander |first1=Harriet |last2=Lawler |first2=David |date=June 13, 2016 |title='We thought it was part of the music': how the Pulse nightclub massacre unfolded in Orlando |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/12/we-thought-it-was-part-of-the-music-how-the-pulse-nightclub-mass/ |work=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613041348/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/12/we-thought-it-was-part-of-the-music-how-the-pulse-nightclub-mass/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> A recently discharged [[United States Marine Corps|Marine]] veteran working as a nightclub bouncer immediately recognized the sounds as gunfire, which he described as \"high caliber\", and jumped over a locked door behind which dozens of people were hidden and paralyzed by fear, then opened a latched door behind them, allowing approximately 70 people to escape.<ref>{{cite news |last=Schogol |first=Jeff |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Marine vet's quick actions saved dozens of lives during Orlando nightclub shooting |url=http://www.marinecorpstimes.com/story/military/2016/06/14/marine-vets-quick-actions-saved-dozens-lives-during-orlando-nightclub-shooting/85860320/ |work=Marine Corps Times |access-date=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818055429/http://www.marinecorpstimes.com/story/military/2016/06/14/marine-vets-quick-actions-saved-dozens-lives-during-orlando-nightclub-shooting/85860320/ |archivedate=August 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Holley |first=Peter |date=June 15, 2016 |title=How a heroic Marine's military training helped him save dozens from Orlando gunman |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/checkpoint/wp/2016/06/15/how-a-heroic-marines-military-training-helped-him-save-dozens-from-orlando-gunman/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160709083625/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/checkpoint/wp/2016/06/15/how-a-heroic-marines-military-training-helped-him-save-dozens-from-orlando-gunman/ |archivedate=July 9, 2016}}</ref> Many described a scene of panic and confusion caused by the loud music and darkness. One person shielded herself by hiding inside a bathroom and covering herself with bodies. A bartender said she took cover beneath the glass bar. At least one patron tried to help those who were hit.<ref name=\"cnn\" /> According to a man trapped inside a bathroom with fifteen other patrons, Mateen fired sixteen times into the bathroom, through the closed door, killing at least two and wounding several others.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/pulse-patron-tried-calming-others-during-massacre-new-911-calls-reveal/ |title=Pulse patron tried calming others during massacre new 911 calls reveal |publisher=CBS News |agency=Associated Press |date=November 15, 2016 |accessdate=November 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117160035/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/pulse-patron-tried-calming-others-during-massacre-new-911-calls-reveal/ |archivedate=November 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAccording to one of the hostages, Mateen entered a bathroom in the nightclub's northwest side and opened fire on the people hiding there, wounding several. The hostage, who had taken cover inside a stall with others, was injured by two bullets and struck with flying pieces of a wall hit by stray bullets. Mateen's rifle then jammed briefly, at which point he switched to using a handgun.<ref name=\"WPPoliceResponse\" /><ref name=\"GMA.Recounts\">{{cite news |last=Mohney |first=Gillian |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Hostage Injured at Orlando Nightclub Recounts Hours of Pain and Fear With Gunman |url=https://www.yahoo.com/gma/hostage-injured-orlando-nightclub-recounts-hours-pain-fear-000135444--abc-news-topstories.html |work=ABC News |via=Yahoo! News (GMA) |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201042707/https://www.yahoo.com/gma/hostage-injured-orlando-nightclub-recounts-hours-pain-fear-000135444--abc-news-topstories.html |archivedate=December 1, 2017}}</ref><ref name=abcnews2>{{cite web |last1=Katersky |first1=Aaron |last2=Withers |first2=Scott |last3=Kennedy |first3=Scottye |last4=Blake |first4=Paul |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/alive-raise-hand-desperate-rescuer-pulse-nightclub/story?id=46797935 |title='If you're alive, raise your hand' desperate rescuer said in Pulse nightclub |work=ABC News |date=April 14, 2017 |accessdate=April 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414193357/http://abcnews.go.com/US/alive-raise-hand-desperate-rescuer-pulse-nightclub/story?id=46797935 |archivedate=April 14, 2017}}</ref> Two survivors quoted Mateen as saying, \"I don't have a problem with black people\",<ref>{{cite news |last=Hennessy-Fiske |first=Molly |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Survivor on Orlando gunman: 'He was not going to stop killing people until he was killed' |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-nightclub-restroom-survivors-20160614-snap-story.html |work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=June 15, 2016 |quote=[Patience Carter, a hostage] continued: 'There was an African American man in the stall with us... he said, 'Yes, there are about six or seven of us.' The gunman responded back to him saying that, 'You know, I don't have a problem with black people, this is about my country. You guys suffered enough.' |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615004359/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-nightclub-restroom-survivors-20160614-snap-story.html |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Orlando shooting survivor recounts terrifying moments |url=http://www.fox29.com/news/158721816-story |work=Fox 29 |date=June 13, 2016 |access-date=June 15, 2016 |quote='I could hear him talking, and he said, \"I don't have a problem with black people. It's nothing personal. I'm just tired of your people killing my people in Iraq\",' Parker explained. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615122259/http://www.fox29.com/news/158721816-story |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> and that he \"wouldn't stop his assault until America stopped bombing his country\".<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Orlando survivor: Gunman tried to spare black people |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-survivor-patience-carter-gunman-tried-to-spare-black-people/ |publisher=CBS News |date=June 14, 2016 |access-date=June 15, 2016 |quote=Carter, 20 years old, had fled into the bathroom of Pulse nightclub during the Orlando massacre, and as the situation was winding down, she said the gunman told police negotiators on the phone he pledged his allegiance to ISIS and wouldn't stop his assault until America stopped bombing his country. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615121937/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-survivor-patience-carter-gunman-tried-to-spare-black-people/ |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> Other survivors heard Mateen claim he had explosives as well as snipers stationed around the club.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hennessy-Fiske |first=Molly |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Survivor on Orlando gunman: 'He was not going to stop killing people until he was killed' |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-nightclub-restroom-survivors-20160614-snap-story.html |work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615004359/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-nightclub-restroom-survivors-20160614-snap-story.html |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\nPatrons trapped inside called or texted 9-1-1 to warn of the possible presence of explosives.<ref name=\"NYTimes.Strap\">{{cite news |last1=Robles |first1=Frances |last2=P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |first2=Richard |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Omar Mateen Told Police He'd Strap Bombs to Hostages, Orlando Mayor Says |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/16/us/orlando-shooting.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615180906/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/16/us/orlando-shooting.html |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Emergency response===\nIn the next 45 minutes, about 100 officers from the OPD and the [[Orange County Sheriff's Office (Florida)|Orange County Sheriff's Office]] were dispatched to the scene.<ref name=\"CNN.Timeline\" /> Among the earliest [[first responders]] to arrive were a firefighter crew from {{nowrap|Fire Station 5}} and two supporting firefighter paramedics from {{nowrap|Fire Station 7}}. Eighty Fire and [[Emergency Medical Services]] personnel from the Orlando Fire Department were deployed during the entire incident.<ref>{{cite news |last=Burch |first=Audra D.S. |date=July 2, 2016 |title=The paramedics of Pulse heard the gunfire, then saw something they never thought possible |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/state/florida/article87364892.html |work=Miami Herald |access-date=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160730190716/http://www.miamiherald.com/news/state/florida/article87364892.html |archivedate=July 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAt {{nowrap|2:09 a.m.}}, several minutes after gunfire began, the club posted on its [[Facebook]] page, \"Everyone get out of pulse {{sic}}<!--Direct quote; lowercase \"p\" is correct.--> and keep running.\"<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Timeline\" /> At {{nowrap|2:22 a.m.}}, Mateen placed a 9-1-1 call in which he mentioned the [[Boston Marathon bombing|Boston Marathon bombers]]\u2014[[Tamerlan Tsarnaev|Tamerlan]] and [[Dzhokhar Tsarnaev]]\u2014as his \"homeboys\" and made a reference to [[Moner Mohammad Abu Salha]], an American citizen who died in a suicide bombing in Syria in 2014.<ref name=\"CNN.Timeline\">{{cite news |last1=Stapleton |first1=AnneClaire |last2=Ellis |first2=Ralph |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Timeline of Orlando nightclub shooting |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/12/us/orlando-shooting-timeline/ |publisher=CNN |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613115710/http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/12/us/orlando-shooting-timeline/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Barrett-WSJ\">{{cite news |last1=Barrett |first1=Devlin |last2=Entous |first2=Adam |last3=Cullison |first3=Alan |date=June 12, 2016 |title=FBI Twice Probed Orlando Gunman |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-gunman-was-twice-probed-by-fbi-1465761322 |work=The Wall Street Journal |access-date=June 21, 2016 |url-access=subscription  |quote=Law-enforcement officials said that investigation was prompted because Abu-Salha and Mateen attended the same mosque. Investigators concluded that while the two men probably knew each other's names and faces... |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160620125427/http://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-gunman-was-twice-probed-by-fbi-1465761322 |archivedate=June 20, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"wburFBI\">{{cite news |title=FBI Boston Chief: In Call, Mateen Referred To Tsarnaevs As His 'Homeboys' |url=http://www.wbur.org/news/2016/06/13/mateen-orlando-tsarnaevs-monday |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=WBUR News |date=June 13, 2016 |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614113944/http://www.wbur.org/news/2016/06/13/mateen-orlando-tsarnaevs-monday |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> Mateen said he was inspired by Abu Salha's death for the [[Al-Nusra Front]] targeting [[Syrian Armed Forces|Syrian government troops]] (a mutual enemy of the two Salafist groups, despite their history of violence with each other), and [[Bay'ah|swore allegiance]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/06/orlando-terrorist-swore-allegiance-to-islamic-states-abu-bakr-al-baghdadi.php |title=Orlando terrorist swore allegiance to Islamic State's Abu Bakr al Baghdadi |last=Joscelyn |first=Thomas |date=June 20, 2016 |work=[[The Long War Journal]] |access-date=July 3, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625012652/http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/06/orlando-terrorist-swore-allegiance-to-islamic-states-abu-bakr-al-baghdadi.php |archivedate=June 25, 2016}}</ref> to ISIL leader al-Baghdadi.<ref name=\"businessinsidercomey\">{{cite web |last1=Bertrand |first1=Natasha |last2=Engel |first2=Pamela |date=June 13, 2016 |title=The FBI director just painted a bizarre picture of the man behind the worst mass shooting in US history |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/james-comey-orlando-shooting-omar-mateen-fbi-2016-6 |website=Business Insider |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614122903/http://www.businessinsider.com/james-comey-orlando-shooting-omar-mateen-fbi-2016-6 |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> The FBI said that Mateen and Abu Salha had attended the same mosque and knew each other \"casually\".<ref>{{cite news |first=Mark |last=Mazzetti |first2=Eric |last2=Lichtblau |first3=Alan |last3=Blinder |title=Omar Mateen, Twice Scrutinized by F.B.I., Shows Threat of Lone Terrorists |date=June 13, 2016 |accessdate=July 8, 2016 |website=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/14/us/politics/orlando-shooting-omar-mateen.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716151536/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/14/us/politics/orlando-shooting-omar-mateen.html |archivedate=July 16, 2016}}</ref> Mateen made two other [[9-1-1]] calls during the shooting.<ref name=\"wburFBI\" /> Numerous 9-1-1 calls were made by the patrons inside the nightclub around this time.<ref name=\"9-1-1 Calls by Pulse Patrons\">{{cite news |last1=Lotan |first1=Gal Tziperman |last2=Allen |first2=Stephanie |date=June 28, 2016 |title=Dispatchers heard gunshots, screams, moans in Pulse 911 calls |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-timeline-records-20160628-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 1, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629191413/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-timeline-records-20160628-story.html |archivedate=June 29, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAfter the initial rounds of gunfire between Mateen and Gruler, six officers shot out a large glass window and followed the sound of shooting to the bathroom area. When Mateen stuck his head out from one of the bathrooms, at least two officers shot at him. After the gunfire stopped, they were ordered to hold position instead of storming the bathroom, according to one of the officers.<ref name=\"MozingoPearceWilkinson\" /><ref name=\"WPPoliceResponse\">{{cite news |last1=Goldman |first1=Adam |last2=Berman |first2=Mark |date=August 1, 2016 |title='They took too damn long': Inside the police response to the Orlando shooting |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/they-took-too-damn-long-inside-the-police-response-to-the-orlando-shooting/2016/08/01/67a66130-5447-11e6-88eb-7dda4e2f2aec_story.html |work=The Washington Post |access-date=August 1, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160801182311/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/they-took-too-damn-long-inside-the-police-response-to-the-orlando-shooting/2016/08/01/67a66130-5447-11e6-88eb-7dda4e2f2aec_story.html |archivedate=August 1, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"HausMcCrum\">{{cite news |last1=Hauslohner |first1=Abigail |last2=McCrummen |first2=Stephanie |date=June 21, 2016 |title=Orlando shooting: A quick response and then a long wait |url=http://www.nola.com/politics/index.ssf/2016/06/orlando_shooting_a_quick_respo.html |work=The Washington Post |publisher=The Times-Picayune |access-date=July 8, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160623150301/http://www.nola.com/politics/index.ssf/2016/06/orlando_shooting_a_quick_respo.html |archivedate=June 23, 2016}}</ref> After about 15 to 20 minutes, [[SWAT]] arrived and had the officers withdraw as the officers were \"not really in tactical gear\". SWAT then took over the operation.<ref name=\"HausMcCrum\" /> When asked why the officers didn't proceed to the bathroom and engage Mateen, Orlando Police Chief John Mina said it was because Mateen \"went from an active shooter to a barricaded gunman\" and had hostages. He also noted, \"If he had continued shooting, our officers would have went in there.\"<ref name=\"WPPoliceResponse\" /> At that time, the last shot by Mateen was fired between {{nowrap|2:10 a.m.}} and {{nowrap|2:18 a.m.}}<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Question\">{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-next-pulse-911-calls-released-20161116-story.html |title=Victims question rescue efforts in latest Pulse 911 calls |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=November 16, 2016 |accessdate=November 16, 2016 |first=Christal |last=Hayes |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117042104/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-next-pulse-911-calls-released-20161116-story.html |archivedate=November 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\nRescues of people trapped inside the nightclub commenced and continued throughout the night. Because so many people were lying on the dance floor, one rescuing officer demanded, \"If you're alive, raise your hand.\"<ref name=orlandosentinel1/> By {{nowrap|2:35 a.m.}}, police had managed to extract nearly all of the injured from the nightclub. Those who remained included the hostages held by Mateen in the bathroom, as well as a dozen people who were hiding inside dressing rooms.<ref name=washingtonpost1>{{cite web |last1=Berman |first1=Mark |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-nation/wp/2017/04/14/if-youre-alive-raise-your-hand-orlando-police-detail-response-to-pulse-nightclub-attack/ |title='If you're alive, raise your hand': Orlando police detail response to Pulse nightclub attack |work=The Washington Post |date=April 14, 2017 |accessdate=April 14, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414203710/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-nation/wp/2017/04/14/if-youre-alive-raise-your-hand-orlando-police-detail-response-to-pulse-nightclub-attack/ |archivedate=April 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Phone calls and negotiations===\nAt {{nowrap|2:45 a.m.}}, Mateen called [[News 13]] of Orlando and said, \"I'm the shooter. It's me. I am the shooter.\" He then said he was carrying out the shooting on the behalf of ISIL and began speaking rapidly in Arabic.<ref>{{cite news |last=Fais |first=Scott |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Mateen to News 13 producer: 'I'm the shooter. It's me.' |url=http://www.mynews13.com/content/news/cfnews13/news/article.html/content/news/articles/cfn/2016/6/14/orlando_shooting_oma.html |publisher=News 13 |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616004253/https://www.mynews13.com/content/news/cfnews13/news/article.html/content/news/articles/cfn/2016/6/14/orlando_shooting_oma.html |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Miller |first=Michael E. |date=June 15, 2016 |title='I'm the shooter. It's me': Gunman called local TV station during attack, station says |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2016/06/15/im-the-shooter-its-me-gunman-called-local-tv-station-during-attack-station-says/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615155427/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2016/06/15/im-the-shooter-its-me-gunman-called-local-tv-station-during-attack-station-says/ |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> Mateen also said the shooting was \"triggered\" by a U.S.-led bombing strike in Iraq that killed [[Abu Wahib]], an ISIL military commander, on {{nowrap|May 6}}.<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Reveal\">{{cite news |first1=Caitlin |last1=Doornbos |title=Transcripts of 911 calls reveal Pulse shooter's terrorist motives |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-911-calls-released-orlando-shooting-20170922-story.html |accessdate=September 28, 2016 |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=September 23, 2016 |quote=Mateen referred to a U.S.-led air strike on May 6 that killed Abu Wahib, an ISIS military commander in Iraq, and three other jihadists, according to the Pentagon. 'That's what triggered it, OK?' Mateen said. 'They should have not bombed and killed Abu [Wahib].' |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160926204945/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-911-calls-released-orlando-shooting-20170922-story.html |archivedate=September 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\nA [[crisis negotiator]] was present as Mateen was holed up inside and holding hostages.<ref name=\"WFTV ABC\" /><ref name=\"Reuters\">{{cite news |last=Liston |first=Barbara |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Fifty people killed in massacre at Florida gay nightclub: police |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-nightclub-idUSKCN0YY08B |agency=Reuters |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612084344/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-nightclub-idUSKCN0YY08B |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> Officers initially believed he was armed with a \"suspicious device\" that posed a threat, but it was later revealed to be a battery that fell out of an exit sign or smoke detector.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=50 Dead, 53 Hurt In Orlando Nightclub Shooting |url=http://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2016/06/12/50-dead-53-hurt-in-orlando-nightclub-shooting/ |work=CBS Local Minnesota |agency=Associated Press |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613022219/http://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2016/06/12/50-dead-53-hurt-in-orlando-nightclub-shooting/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nPolice hostage negotiators spoke with Mateen by telephone three times between {{nowrap|2:48 a.m.}} and {{nowrap|3:27 a.m.}}<ref name=\"fbitranscript\">{{cite press release |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Investigative Update Regarding Pulse Nightclub Shooting |url=https://www.fbi.gov/tampa/press-releases/2016/investigative-update-regarding-pulse-nightclub-shooting |location=Tampa, Florida |publisher=Federal Bureau of Investigation |agency=Tampa Division |date=June 20, 2016 |access-date=June 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160620162229/https://www.fbi.gov/tampa/press-releases/2016/investigative-update-regarding-pulse-nightclub-shooting |archivedate=June 20, 2016}}</ref> He claimed during one of the calls that he had bombs strapped to his body.<ref name=\"WFTV ABC\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Records: Gunshots, moaning heard by dispatchers as terror unfolded in Pulse |url=http://www.wftv.com/news/pulse-shooting/documents-gunshots-moaning-heard-by-dispatchers-as-terror-unfolded-in-pulse/370421609 |website=WFTV 9 ABC |date=July 1, 2016 |access-date=July 8, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160702171126/http://www.wftv.com/news/pulse-shooting/documents-gunshots-moaning-heard-by-dispatchers-as-terror-unfolded-in-pulse/370421609 |archivedate=July 2, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"fbitranscript\" /> He also claimed that he \"had a vehicle in the parking lot with enough explosives to take out city blocks.\"<ref name=orlandosentinel1/> At {{nowrap|3:58 a.m.}}, the OPD announced to the public that there was a shooting at the club, and that there were multiple injuries.<ref name=\"CNN.Timeline\" /> At {{nowrap|4:21 a.m.}}, eight of the hostages escaped after police had removed an air conditioning unit from an exterior wall.<ref name=\"CNN.Timeline\" /><ref name=\"fbitranscript\" /> At approximately {{nowrap|4:29 a.m.}}, Mateen told negotiators that he planned to strap explosive vests, similar to those used in the [[November 2015 Paris attacks]], to four hostages, strategically place them in different corners of the building, and detonate them in 15 minutes.<ref name=\"auto000\" /><ref name=\"NYTimes.Strap\" /><ref name=\"WFTV ABC\" /> OPD officers then decided to end negotiations and prepared to blow their way in.<ref name=\"CNN.Timeline\" /><ref name=\"NYT.Visual\" /><ref name=\"WFTV ABC\" />\n\nAt around {{nowrap|2:30 a.m.}}, Mateen's second wife\u2014after receiving a call from her mother at approximately {{nowrap|2:00 a.m.}} asking where her husband was\u2014sent a text message to Mateen asking where he was. Mateen texted back asking her if she had seen the news. After she replied, \"No?\", Mateen responded, \"I love you, babe.\" According to one source, she texted him back at one point saying that she loved him. She also called him several times during the standoff, but he did not answer. She found out about what was happening at {{nowrap|4:00 a.m.}} after the police told her to come out of her house with her hands up.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Yan |first1=Holly |last2=Brown |first2=Pamela |last3=Perez |first3=Evan |date=June 16, 2016 |title=Orlando shooter texted wife during attack, source says |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/16/us/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen/ |publisher=CNN |access-date=June 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616235854/https://www.cnn.com/2016/06/16/us/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Mohyeldin |first1=Ayman |last2=Williams |first2=Pete |last3=Helsel |first3=Phil |date=June 17, 2016 |title=Orlando Gunman Omar Mateen and Wife Exchanged Texts During Rampage |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/orlando-gunman-omar-mateen-wife-exchanged-texts-during-rampage-n594011 |work=NBC News |access-date=July 17, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160717080813/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/orlando-gunman-omar-mateen-wife-exchanged-texts-during-rampage-n594011 |archivedate=July 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\nA survivor of the shooting recalled Mateen saying he wanted the United States to \"stop bombing his country\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Smith |first=David |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Omar Mateen's wife may be charged if she knew he was planning Orlando shooting |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/14/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-omar-mateen-wife |work=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615001910/http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/14/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-omar-mateen-wife |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Orlando survivor: Gunman tried to spare black people |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-survivor-patience-carter-gunman-tried-to-spare-black-people/ |publisher=[[CBS News]] |date=June 14, 2016 |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615121937/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-survivor-patience-carter-gunman-tried-to-spare-black-people/ |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> The FBI said Mateen \"told a negotiator to tell America to stop bombing Syria and Iraq and that was why he was 'out here right now'\".<ref name=\"fbitranscript\" /> During the siege, Mateen made Internet searches on the shooting, while police dispatched a tactical robot to discreetly enter the restroom and allow them to communicate with hostages via two-way audio.<ref name=\"auto000\" />\n\n===Rescue and resolution===\n[[File:Orange County Sheriff's Office body-camera video from inside the Pulse Nightclub, June 2016.ogg|thumb|Orange County Sheriff's Office body-camera footage, showing police responding to the massacre.]]\n[[File:20160612PulseNightclubExteriorHoles.JPG|thumb|Pulse nightclub exterior, showing holes made by the [[Lenco BearCat|BearCat]] and bullet holes]]\n\nThe FBI reported that no shots were heard between the time Mateen stopped exchanging gunfire with the first responders and {{nowrap|5:02 a.m.}}, when Orlando police began breaching the building's wall.<ref name=\"fbitranscript\" /> Just before the breach, Mateen entered a women's bathroom where the hostages were hiding and opened fire, killing a man who sacrificed his life to save the woman behind him and at least one other, according to witnesses.<ref name=\"WPPoliceResponse\" /><ref name=\"GMA.Recounts\" />\n\nAt {{nowrap|5:07 a.m.}}, fourteen SWAT officers\u2014after failing to blow open a big enough hole in the bathroom's exterior wall using a bomb due to the wall's structure<ref name=\"auto000\" />\u2014successfully breached the building when a policeman drove a [[BearCat]] armored vehicle through a wall in the northern bathroom. They then used two [[flashbangs]] to distract Mateen, and shot at him.<ref name=\"MozingoPearceWilkinson\" /><ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Timeline\">{{cite news |last=Lotan |first=Gal Tziperman |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Orlando mass shooting: Timeline of events |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-tick-tock-20160613-story.html |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613112124/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-tick-tock-20160613-story.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref name=washingtonpost1/><ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Autopsy\">{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/omar-mateen/os-pulse-shooting-mateen-autopsy-20160805-story.html |title=Autopsy: Pulse shooter Omar Mateen shot eight times |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=August 5, 2016 |accessdate=August 6, 2016 |first=Caitlin |last=Doornbos |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806152723/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/omar-mateen/os-pulse-shooting-mateen-autopsy-20160805-story.html |archivedate=August 6, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Sarkissian |first=Arek |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Officers may have shot Orlando club patrons |url=http://www.kare11.com/news/nation-now/orlando-shooting/officers-may-have-shot-orlando-club-patrons_/243788446 |work=KARE 11 |access-date=July 2, 2016}}</ref> The breach drew Mateen out into the hallway, and at {{nowrap|5:14 a.m.}}, he engaged the officers. He was shot eight times and killed in the resulting shootout, which involved at least eleven officers who fired a total of about 150 bullets.<ref name=washingtonpost1/><ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Autopsy\"/><ref name=\"BBC summary\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Orlando gay nightclub shooting 'an act of terror and hate' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-36513658 |agency=BBC News |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612225613/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-36513658 |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"FDLEWrapUp\">{{cite news |last=Harris |first=David |date=July 13, 2016 |title=Official: FDLE to wrap up Pulse shooting investigation within month |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-fdle-response-letter-20160713-story.html |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160715184454/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-fdle-response-letter-20160713-story.html |archivedate=July 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/pulse-nightclub-shooter-omar-mateen-000000431.html |title=Pulse nightclub shooter Omar Mateen shot eight times, autopsy reveals |work=Yahoo! News |date=August 5, 2016 |accessdate=August 5, 2016 |first=Jason |last=Sickles |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806151838/https://www.yahoo.com/news/pulse-nightclub-shooter-omar-mateen-000000431.html |archivedate=August 6, 2016}}</ref> He was reported \"down\" at {{nowrap|5:17 a.m.}}<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Autopsy\"/>\n\nAt {{nowrap|5:05 a.m.}}, the police said a [[bomb squad]] had set off a [[controlled explosion]].<ref name=\"CNN.Timeline\" /><ref name=\"USAToday\">{{cite news |last1=Solis |first1=Steph |last2=Bacon |first2=John |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Islamic State linked to worst mass shooting in U.S. history |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2016/06/12/shooting-orlando-club/85785254/ |work=USA Today |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612090931/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2016/06/12/shooting-orlando-club/85785254/ |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> At {{nowrap|5:53 a.m.}}, the Orlando police posted on [[Twitter]], \"Pulse Shooting: The shooter inside the club is dead.\"<ref name=\"CNN.Timeline\" /> Thirty hostages were freed during the police operation.<ref name=\"MozingoPearceWilkinson\" /><ref name=\"guardian1\">{{cite news |last=Lyons |first=Kate |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Orlando Pulse club attack: gunman identified as police investigate motive |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/12/orlando-shooting-nightclub-pulse-gunman |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612100242/http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/12/orlando-shooting-nightclub-pulse-gunman |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> The survivors were searched by police for guns and explosives.<ref name=\"NYTimes.Strap\" />\n\n==Casualties{{anchor|Victims}}==\nFifty people died in the incident, including Mateen, and another 58 were injured, 53 by gunfire and five by other causes. Some of the survivors suffered critical injuries.<ref name=\"auto000\" /><ref name=orlandosentinel1/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Stolberg |first1=Sheryl Gay |last2=P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |first2=Richard |author-link2=Richard P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Orlando Shooting Survivors Cope With the Trauma of Good Fortune |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/15/us/orlando-shooting.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 14, 2016 |quote=The slaughter early Sunday left 49 victims dead, in addition to the gunman, and 53 wounded ... More than 30 of the wounded remained in hospitals on Tuesday, including at least six who were in critical condition. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614163332/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/15/us/orlando-shooting.html |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> Many underwent surgery.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Orlando shooting victims arrived by 'truckloads,' doctor says |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/ct-orlando-nightclub-shooting-20160614-story.html |work=Chicago Tribune |date=June 14, 2016 |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614202235/http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/ct-orlando-nightclub-shooting-20160614-story.html |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> Thirty-nine, including Mateen, were pronounced dead at the scene, and eleven at local hospitals.<ref name=\"cnn\" /><ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Timeline\" /> Of the thirty-eight victims to die at the scene, twenty died on the stage area and dance floor, nine in the nightclub's northern bathroom, four in the southern bathroom, three on the stage, one at the front lobby, and one out on a patio.<ref name=orlandosentinel1/><ref name=abcnews2/> At least five of the dead were not killed during the initial volley of gunfire by Mateen, but during the hostage situation in the bathroom.<ref name=washingtonpost1/>\n\nMost of the injured\u201444 people\u2014were taken to the [[Orlando Regional Medical Center]] (ORMC), the primary regional [[trauma center]] three blocks away; twelve others went to [[Florida Hospital Orlando]].<ref name=\"NYTInitial\">{{cite news |last1=Alvarez |first1=Lizette |last2=P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |first2=Richard |author-link2=Richard P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Orlando Gunman Attacks Gay Nightclub, Leaving 50 Dead |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/orlando-nightclub-shooting.html |access-date=June 12, 2016 |newspaper=The New York Times |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612102027/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/orlando-nightclub-shooting.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"AutopsiesDischarged\">{{cite news |last=Miller |first=Naseem S. |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Orlando shooting autopsies complete, more survivors discharged |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-shooting-injury-update-20160615-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617181408/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-shooting-injury-update-20160615-story.html |archivedate=June 17, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/08/25/491348765/orlando-hospitals-say-they-wont-bill-victims-of-pulse-nightclub-shooting |title=Orlando Hospitals Say They Won't Bill Victims Of Pulse Nightclub Shooting |work=NPR |date=August 25, 2016 |accessdate=September 6, 2016 |first=Camila |last=Domonoske |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160905233148/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/08/25/491348765/orlando-hospitals-say-they-wont-bill-victims-of-pulse-nightclub-shooting |archivedate=September 5, 2016}}</ref> Nine of ORMC's patients died there, and by {{nowrap|June 14}}, 27 remained hospitalized, with six in critical condition.<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Discharged\">{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-last-hospitalized-pulse-survivor-is-discharged-20160906-story.html |title=Last hospitalized Pulse shooting survivor discharged after nearly 3 months |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=September 6, 2016 |accessdate=September 6, 2016 |first=Naseem S. |last=Miller |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160907011713/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-last-hospitalized-pulse-survivor-is-discharged-20160906-story.html |archivedate=September 7, 2016}}</ref> ORMC performed a total of 76 surgeries on its patients.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/orlando-shooting-survivor-discharged-hospital/story?id=41904465 |title=Last Orlando Shooting Survivor Discharged From Hospital |work=ABC News |date=September 6, 2016 |accessdate=September 6, 2016 |first=Julia |last=Jacobo |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160907051246/http://abcnews.go.com/US/orlando-shooting-survivor-discharged-hospital/story?id=41904465 |archivedate=September 7, 2016}}</ref> The last of the injured was discharged from ORMC on {{nowrap|September 6}}, nearly three months after the shooting.<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Discharged\"/>\n\nAutopsies of the 49 dead were completed by the Orange County Medical Examiner's Office by {{nowrap|June 14}},<ref name=\"AutopsiesDischarged\" /> and their results were released in early August. According to the autopsy reports, many of the victims were shot multiple times in the front or side, and from a short distance. More than a third were shot in the head, and most had multiple bullet wounds and were likely shot more than {{convert|3|ft|abbr=off|sp=us}} away. In total, there were over 200 gunshot wounds.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-autopsy-reports-20160805-story.html |title=Pulse families get some answers from autopsies |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=August 5, 2016 |accessdate=August 6, 2016 |first=Christal |last=Hayes |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806162123/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-autopsy-reports-20160805-story.html |archivedate=August 6, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Harris |first=David |date=August 8, 2016 |title=Final autopsies of Pulse victims released |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-more-autopsies-20160808-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=August 8, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809224602/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-more-autopsies-20160808-story.html |archivedate=August 9, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Toppo |first=Greg |date=August 8, 2016 |title=Autopsies: victims of Pulse nightclub shooting shot more than 200 times total |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/08/08/autopsies-victims-pulse-nightclub-shooting/88431710/ |work=USA Today |access-date=August 8, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809001611/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/08/08/autopsies-victims-pulse-nightclub-shooting/88431710/ |archivedate=August 9, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Schneider |first=Mike |date=August 9, 2016 |title=Autopsies: A third of Pulse nightclub victims shot in head |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/autopsies-third-pulse-nightclub-victims-shot-head-191017256.html |work=Yahoo! News |agency=The Associated Press |access-date=August 10, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160810183840/https://www.yahoo.com/news/autopsies-third-pulse-nightclub-victims-shot-head-191017256.html |archivedate=August 10, 2016}}</ref>\n\nA responding SWAT officer received a minor head injury when a bullet hit his Kevlar helmet.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Photo released shows injury to officer who was shot in head, but protected by helmet |url=http://www.wftv.com/web/wftv/news/pulse-shooting/photo-released-shows-injury-to-officer-who-was-shot-in-head-but-protected-by-helmet/340126409 |work=WFTV 9 ABC |publisher=Cox Media Group |date=June 29, 2016}}</ref> Pulse was hosting Latin Night; over 90% of the victims were of [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic]] background, and half of those were of [[Puerto Ricans in the United States|Puerto Rican descent]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Golshan |first1=Tara |last2=Nelson |first2=Libby |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Pulse gay nightclub shooting in Orlando: what we know |url=https://www.vox.com/2016/6/12/11911616/pulse-gay-nightclub-shooting-in-orlando-what-we-know |work=Vox |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613110639/http://www.vox.com/2016/6/12/11911616/pulse-gay-nightclub-shooting-in-orlando-what-we-know |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Sullivan |first1=Kevin |last2=Hern\u00e1ndez |first2=Arelis R. |title=Orlando's Latino community hit hard by massacre at nightclub |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/among-the-dead-in-orlando-massacre-many-from-the-latino-community/2016/06/13/8192e3a4-3186-11e6-8758-d58e76e11b12_story.html |work=The Washington Post |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614135132/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/among-the-dead-in-orlando-massacre-many-from-the-latino-community/2016/06/13/8192e3a4-3186-11e6-8758-d58e76e11b12_story.html |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> Four [[Dominican Republic|Dominicans]] and three Mexican citizens were killed;<ref>{{cite news |last=Cabral |first=Ariel |date=June 16, 2016 |title=Identifican a un cuarto dominicano muerto en atentados Orlando |trans-title=A fourth Dominican was killed in Orlando attacks |url=http://www.hoy.com.do/identifican-a-un-cuarto-dominicano-muerto-en-atentados-orlando/ |language=Spanish |publisher=Hoy |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160704224404/http://hoy.com.do/identifican-a-un-cuarto-dominicano-muerto-en-atentados-orlando/ |archive-date=July 4, 2016 |access-date=July 4, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Hays |first=Chris |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Consulate eager to help Mexican nationals killed in Orlando nightclub shooting |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-mexican-consulate-orlando-nightclub-shooting-20160613-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615115857/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-mexican-consulate-orlando-nightclub-shooting-20160613-story.html |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> three Colombians and two Canadians were injured.<ref>{{cite news |last=Alsema |first=Adriaan |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Three Colombians injured in Orlando nightclub shooting |url=http://colombiareports.com/three-colombians-injured-orlando-massacre |work=Colombia Reports |access-date=June 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161004170625/http://colombiareports.com/three-colombians-injured-orlando-massacre |archivedate=October 4, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Two Canadians injured in Orlando shooting fear for their lives |url=https://montrealgazette.com/news/two-canadians-injured-in-orlando-shooting |work=[[The Gazette (Montreal)|Montreal Gazette]] |date=June 15, 2016 |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615231839/http://montrealgazette.com/news/two-canadians-injured-in-orlando-shooting |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> An off-duty [[United States Army Reserve]] captain at the club who was not in uniform was also killed.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Orlando Casualties Include Army Reserve Captain |url=http://www.defense.gov/News-Article-View/Article/799266/orlando-casualties-include-army-reserve-captain |work=Department of Defense News |agency=Defense Media Activity |date=June 14, 2016 |access-date=June 26, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615121430/http://www.defense.gov/News-Article-View/Article/799266/orlando-casualties-include-army-reserve-captain |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Kevin |first=Lilley |date=June 16, 2016 |title=Will Reserve captain killed in Orlando massacre earn Purple Heart? |url=http://www.armytimes.com/story/military/2016/06/16/reserve-captain-killed-orlando-massacre-earn-purple-heart/86000612/ |work=Army Times |access-date=June 27, 2016 |quote=Capt. Antonio D. Brown wasn't on duty or in uniform when he was shot dead early Sunday morning...}}</ref>\n\nThe attack is the second-deadliest mass shooting by a single shooter in United States history, behind the [[2017 Las Vegas shooting]];<ref>{{cite web |title=The deadliest shootings in U.S. history |website=Fox News |date=October 2, 2017 |url=http://www.foxnews.com/us/2017/10/02/deadliest-shootings-in-u-s-history.html | access-date=October 2, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002143019/http://www.foxnews.com/us/2017/10/02/deadliest-shootings-in-u-s-history.html |archivedate=October 2, 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Las Vegas shooting now tops list of worst mass shootings in U.S. history |website=USA TODAY |date=October 2, 2017 |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2017/10/02/worst-mass-shootings-u-s-history/722254001/ | access-date=October 2, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002114412/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2017/10/02/worst-mass-shootings-u-s-history/722254001/ |archivedate=October 2, 2017 }}</ref> prior to the Las Vegas shooting, the Pulse shooting had been the deadliest mass shooting in U.S. history.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ingraham |first=Christopher |date=June 12, 2016 |title=In the modern history of mass shootings in America, Orlando is the deadliest |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2016/06/12/in-the-modern-history-of-mass-shootings-in-america-orlando-is-the-absolute-worst/ |work=The Washington Post |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180201080534/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2016/06/12/in-the-modern-history-of-mass-shootings-in-america-orlando-is-the-absolute-worst/ |archivedate=February 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Peralta |first=Eyder |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Putting 'Deadliest Mass Shooting In U.S. History' Into Some Historical Context |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/06/13/481884291/putting-deadliest-mass-shooting-in-u-s-history-into-some-historical-context |publisher=NPR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171022063734/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/06/13/481884291/putting-deadliest-mass-shooting-in-u-s-history-into-some-historical-context |archivedate=October 22, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Nelson |first=Laura J. |date=June 14, 2016 |title=The worst mass shooting? A look back at massacres in U.S. history |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-mass-shooting-20160614-snap-story.html |work=Los Angeles Times |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615170104/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-mass-shooting-20160614-snap-story.html |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> It is also the deadliest incident of violence against lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender (LGBT) people in the history of the United States\u2014surpassing the 1973 [[UpStairs Lounge arson attack]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Stack |first=Liam |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Before Orlando Shooting, an Anti-Gay Massacre in New Orleans Was Largely Forgotten |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/15/us/upstairs-lounge-new-orleans-fire-orlando-gay-bar.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |quote=The terrorist attack ... was the largest mass killing of gay people in American history, but before Sunday that grim distinction was held by a largely forgotten arson at a New Orleans bar in 1973 that killed 32 people at a time of pernicious anti-gay stigma. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614153827/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/15/us/upstairs-lounge-new-orleans-fire-orlando-gay-bar.html |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref>\u2014and the deadliest terrorist attack in the United States since the [[September 11 attacks]] in 2001.<ref name=\"cnn\">{{cite news |last1=Fantz |first1=Ashley |last2=Karimi |first2=Faith |last3=McLaughlin |first3=Eliott C. |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Orlando shooting: 49 killed, shooter pledged ISIS allegiance |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/12/us/orlando-nightclub-shooting/index.html |publisher=CNN |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612081344/http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/12/us/orlando-nightclub-shooting/index.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Obama: Orlando An Act Of 'Terror And Hate' |url=http://news.sky.com/story/1710904/obama-orlando-an-act-of-terror-and-hate |publisher=Sky News |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612183043/http://news.sky.com/story/1710904/obama-orlando-an-act-of-terror-and-hate |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Swanson |first=Ann |date=June 12, 2016 |title=The Orlando attack could transform the picture of post-9/11 terrorism in America |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2016/06/12/the-orlando-attack-could-transform-the-picture-of-post-911-terrorism-in-america/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612203733/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2016/06/12/the-orlando-attack-could-transform-the-picture-of-post-911-terrorism-in-america/ |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Names of the deceased===\nThe names and ages of the victims killed were confirmed by the City of Orlando after their [[next of kin]] had been notified:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cityoforlando.net/blog/victims/ |title=Victims' Names |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=June 12, 2016 |website=City of Orlando |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612201808/http://www.cityoforlando.net/blog/victims/ |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Teague |first1=Matthew |last2=McCarthy |first2=Ciara |last3=Puglis |first3=Nicole |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Orlando attack victims: the lives cut short in America's deadliest shooting |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/ng-interactive/2016/jun/13/orlando-terror-attack-victims-pulse-nightclub |work=The Guardian |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615005254/http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/ng-interactive/2016/jun/13/orlando-terror-attack-victims-pulse-nightclub |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{div col|colwidth=32em}}<!-- Please note naming conventions\u2014if there are two surnames, regardless of whether it is hyphenated or not, alphabetize by the first surname. For example, Ba