b.archive.org/web/20160613115649/http://bnonews.com/news/index.php/news/id4551 |archivedate=June 13, 2016  }}</ref> an American born in [[New Hyde Park, New York]].<ref name=\"LotanBrinkmannStutzman\">{{cite news |last1=Lotan |first1=Gal Tziperman |last2=Brinkmann |first2=Paul |last3=Stutzman |first3=Rene |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Gunman Omar Mateen visited gay nightclub a dozen times before shooting, witness says |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-nightclub-omar-mateen-profile-20160613-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613215920/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-nightclub-omar-mateen-profile-20160613-story.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Brady |first=Ryan |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Orlando shooter born in New Hyde Park |url=http://www.qchron.com/editions/north/orlando-shooter-born-in-new-hyde-park/article_58b20180-31a0-11e6-b7e9-3b100612b0fb.html |work=[[Queens Chronicle]] |access-date=June 13, 2016}}</ref> His parents were [[Afghan]], and he was raised as a Muslim.<ref name=\"NYTimes.Early\">{{cite news |last1=Blinder |first1=Alan |last2=Healy |first2=Jack |last3=Oppel |first3=Richard A. Jr. |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Omar Mateen: From Early Promise to F.B.I. Surveillance |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/omar-mateen-early-signs-of-promise-then-abuse-and-suspected-terrorist-ties.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613021455/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/omar-mateen-early-signs-of-promise-then-abuse-and-suspected-terrorist-ties.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> At the time of the shooting, he lived in an apartment complex in [[Fort Pierce, Florida]], {{convert|117|mi|abbr=off|sp=us}} from the Pulse nightclub in Orlando.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=50 killed in shooting at Orlando nightclub, Mayor says |url=http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/06/12/florida-authorities-say-multiple-people-have-been-shot-at-orlando-nightclub.html |publisher=FOX News Channel |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612094443/http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/06/12/florida-authorities-say-multiple-people-have-been-shot-at-orlando-nightclub.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"cbslocal\">{{cite news |last=Young |first=Lou |date=June 12, 2016 |title=ISIS Claims Responsibility For Orlando Nightclub Attack That Left 50 Dead |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2016/06/12/orlando-nightclub-shooting/ |publisher=CBS New York |agency=Associated Press |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612145458/https://newyork.cbslocal.com/2016/06/12/orlando-nightclub-shooting/ |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"TCPalm\">{{cite news |last=Jones |first=Elliott |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Omar Mateen's connections to Fort Pierce, Port St. Lucie |url=http://www.tcpalm.com/news/crime/st-lucie-county/who-is-omar-mateen-35140633-45ca-1fbf-e053-0100007fbd3e-382613281.html |publisher=[[Treasure Coast Newspapers]] |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613113858/http://www.tcpalm.com/news/crime/st-lucie-county/who-is-omar-mateen-35140633-45ca-1fbf-e053-0100007fbd3e-382613281.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nMateen's body was buried in the Muslim Cemetery of South Florida, near [[Hialeah Gardens, Florida|Hialeah Gardens]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Allen |first1=Stephanie |last2=Pesantes |first2=Erika |date=June 23, 2016 |title=Pulse shooter Omar Mateen buried near Miami, records show |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/omar-mateen/os-orlando-shooting-omar-mateen-death-20160623-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=August 10, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819022244/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/omar-mateen/os-orlando-shooting-omar-mateen-death-20160623-story.html |archivedate=August 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Personal life===\nFrom October 2006 until April 2007, Mateen trained to be a [[prison guard]] for the [[Florida Department of Corrections]]. As a probationary employee, he received an \"administrative termination (not involving misconduct)\"<ref name=\"Swisher\">{{cite news |last=Swisher |first=Skyler |date=June 16, 2016 |title=Omar Mateen failed multiple times to start career in law enforcement, state records show |url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/florida/fl-omar-mateen-fdle-records-20160616-story.html |newspaper=Sun-Sentinel |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160620064018/http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/florida/fl-omar-mateen-fdle-records-20160616-story.html |archivedate=June 20, 2016}}</ref> upon a warden's recommendation after Mateen joked about bringing a gun to school.<ref name=\"corrections\">{{cite news |last1=Felton |first1=Ryan |last2=Laughland |first2=Oliver |date=June 18, 2016 |title=Orlando shooter was fired for making a gun joke days after Virginia Tech killings |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/17/orlando-gunman-omar-mateen-fired-gun-joke-state-department-corrections |work=The Guardian |access-date=June 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618182513/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/17/orlando-gunman-omar-mateen-fired-gun-joke-state-department-corrections |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref> Mateen unsuccessfully pursued a career in [[law enforcement]], failing to become a [[Florida Highway Patrol|Florida state trooper]] in 2011 and to gain admission to a [[police academy]] in 2015.<ref name=\"Swisher\" /> According to a police academy classmate, Mateen threatened to shoot his classmates at a cookout in 2007 \"after his hamburger touched pork\" in violation of [[Islamic dietary laws]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Berzon |first1=Alexandra |last2=Emshwiller |first2=John R. |date=June 17, 2016 |title=Orlando Shooter Was Dismissed From Academy Over Gun Inquiry, State Says |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-shooter-was-dismissed-from-academy-over-gun-inquiry-state-says-1466213001 |access-date=June 18, 2016 |work=The Wall Street Journal |url-access=subscription  |quote=Susanne Coburn Laforest, a 61-year-old retired corrections officer and former classmate of Mateen, said he threatened to shoot his classmates at a cookout\u2014which she said was held on a gun range\u2014after his hamburger touched pork, in violation of Muslim laws. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618021452/http://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-shooter-was-dismissed-from-academy-over-gun-inquiry-state-says-1466213001 |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Wilber |first1=Del Quentin |last2=Hennessy-Fiske |first2=Molly |date=June 17, 2016 |title=Security videos show killing rampage at Orlando nightclub |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-shooting-investigation-20160617-snap-story.html |work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=June 18, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617223916/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-shooting-investigation-20160617-snap-story.html |archivedate=June 17, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Orlando terrorist reportedly raised suspicion at gun shop weeks before massacre |url=http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/06/16/orlando-terrorist-reportedly-raised-suspicion-at-gun-shop-weeks-before-massacre.html |publisher=Fox News Channel |date=June 16, 2016 |quote=Mateen threatened to shoot his classmates after his hamburger touched pork at an academy cookout. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618110425/http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/06/16/orlando-terrorist-reportedly-raised-suspicion-at-gun-shop-weeks-before-massacre.html |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Mower |first=Lawrence |date=June 17, 2016 |title=Orlando shooting: Prison warden feared mass shooting in 2007 |url=http://www.palmbeachpost.com/news/news/state-regional/orlando-shooting-prison-warden-feared-mass-shootin/nrh4W/ |work=The Palm Beach Post |access-date=June 18, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619215610/http://www.palmbeachpost.com/news/news/state-regional/orlando-shooting-prison-warden-feared-mass-shootin/nrh4W/ |archivedate=June 19, 2016}}</ref> Other witnesses, however, said that they saw Mateen drink alcohol and even \"get drunk\".<ref>{{cite news |title=Before Orlando massacre, killer Omar Mateen visited parents one last time |url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/publicsafety/before-orlando-massacre-killer-omar-mateen-visited-parents-one-last-time/2281507 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614122204/http://www.tampabay.com/news/publicsafety/before-orlando-massacre-killer-omar-mateen-visited-parents-one-last-time/2281507 |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Orlando Shooter Had Visited Pulse Nightclub Before, Witnesses Say |url=http://time.com/4367566/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-omar-mateen/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161213224002/http://time.com/4367566/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-omar-mateen/ |archivedate=December 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nSince 2007, he had been a security guard for [[G4S Secure Solutions]].<ref name=\"TBTWhatWeKnow\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Omar Mateen: What we know, don't know about Orlando nightclub shooter |url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/publicsafety/crime/omar-mateen-what-we-know-about-orlando-nightclub-shooter/2281484 |work=Tampa Bay Times |date=June 13, 2016 |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614115552/http://www.tampabay.com/news/publicsafety/crime/omar-mateen-what-we-know-about-orlando-nightclub-shooter/2281484 |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Schneider |first=Mike |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Worst mass shooting in US history: 50 slain at gay nightclub |url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/435dd4b47ec7403888f74e9c5c3480b5/orlando-police-multiple-injuries-after-nightclub-shooting |agency=Associated Press |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612105911/http://bigstory.ap.org/article/435dd4b47ec7403888f74e9c5c3480b5/orlando-police-multiple-injuries-after-nightclub-shooting |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> The company said two screenings\u2014one conducted upon hiring and the other in 2013\u2014had raised no red flags.<ref>{{cite news |last=Woo |first=Stu |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Orlando Nightclub Shooting Puts G4S in Spotlight Again: U.K.-based security giant that employed Omar Mateen said its vetting had raised no red flags |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-shooter-employer-g4s-saw-no-red-flags-1465817844 |work=The Wall Street Journal |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-access=subscription  |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613121020/http://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-shooter-employer-g4s-saw-no-red-flags-1465817844 |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> Mateen held an active statewide [[firearms license]] and an active security officer license,<ref name=\"ABCWhatWeKknow\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://licensing.freshfromflorida.com/access/individual.aspx?TYPE=INDIVIDUAL&CATEGORY=&COUNTY=00&LICENSE=D%202723758&STATUS=IND_DETAIL |title=Mateen, Omar |author=<!--No by-line--> |website=[[Florida Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services]] |access-date=June 30, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612230614/https://licensing.freshfromflorida.com/access/individual.aspx?TYPE=INDIVIDUAL&CATEGORY=&COUNTY=00&LICENSE=D%202723758&STATUS=IND_DETAIL |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> had passed a [[psychological test]], and had no criminal record.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lotan |first1=Gal Tziperman |last2=Brinkmann |first2=Paul |last3=Stutzman |first3=Rene |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-nightclub-omar-mateen-profile-20160613-story.html |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Witness: Omar Mateen had been at Orlando gay nightclub many times |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613215920/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-nightclub-omar-mateen-profile-20160613-story.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAfter the shooting, the psychologist who reportedly evaluated and cleared Mateen for his firearms license in 2007 by G4S records denied ever meeting him or having lived in Florida at the time, and said she had stopped her practice in Florida since January 2006. G4S admitted Mateen's form had a \"clerical error\" and clarified that he had instead been cleared by another psychologist from the same firm that bought the wrongly-named doctor's practice. This doctor had not interviewed Mateen, but evaluated the results of a standard test used in the screening he undertook before being hired.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ovalle |first=David |date=June 17, 2016 |title='Clerical error' on Orlando killer's psychological eval named wrong doctor |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/state/florida/article84490302.html |work=The Miami Herald |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619144733/http://www.miamiherald.com/news/state/florida/article84490302.html |archivedate=June 19, 2016}}</ref> G4S was subsequently fined for lapses in its psychological testing program (see [[#Aftermath|below]]).\n\nIn 2009, Mateen married his first wife, who left him after a few months; the couple's divorce became final in 2011. Following the nightclub attack, she said Mateen was \"mentally unstable and mentally ill\" and \"obviously disturbed, deeply, and traumatized\", was often [[Domestic violence|physically abusive]], and had a history of using [[Anabolic steroids|steroids]].<ref name=\"NYPost\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Healy |first=Jack |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Sitora Yusufiy, Ex-Wife of Orlando Suspect, Describes Abusive Marriage |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/14/us/sitora-yusufiy-omar-mateen-orlando-shooting.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613163121/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/14/us/sitora-yusufiy-omar-mateen-orlando-shooting.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Goldman |first1=Adam |last2=Tate |first2=Julie |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Ex-wife of suspected Orlando shooter: 'He beat me' |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/ex-wife-of-suspected-orlando-shooter-he-beat-me/2016/06/12/8a1963b4-30b8-11e6-8ff7-7b6c1998b7a0_story.html |work=[[The Washington Post]] |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612174902/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/ex-wife-of-suspected-orlando-shooter-he-beat-me/2016/06/12/8a1963b4-30b8-11e6-8ff7-7b6c1998b7a0_story.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Toppo |first=Greg |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Ex-wife: Orlando shooter 'very short-tempered,' violent |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/06/12/ex-wife-orlando-shooter/85808768/ |work=USA Today |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613032943/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/06/12/ex-wife-orlando-shooter/85808768/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> His autopsy revealed signs of long-term and habitual steroid use, so more toxicology tests were ordered for confirmation.<ref name=\"MateenAutopsy\">{{cite news |last=Otis |first=Ginger Adams |date=July 15, 2016 |title=Orlando nightclub shooter Omar Mateen was HIV-negative and user of steroids, autopsy shows |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/omar-mateen-hiv-negative-habitual-steroid-user-autopsy-article-1.2713155 |work=New York Daily News |access-date=July 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716123413/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/omar-mateen-hiv-negative-habitual-steroid-user-autopsy-article-1.2713155 |archivedate=July 16, 2016}}</ref> As of {{nowrap|July 15}}, 2016, federal investigators were uncertain whether Mateen's steroid use was a factor in the attack.<ref>{{cite news |last=Wilber |first=Del Quentin |date=July 15, 2016 |title=Orlando gunman was HIV-negative, likely a long-term steroid user, autopsy shows |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-mateen-steroid-hiv-20160715-snap-story.html |work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=July 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160715214804/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-mateen-steroid-hiv-20160715-snap-story.html |archivedate=July 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAt the time of the shooting, Mateen was married to his second wife and had a young son.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Slattery |first1=Denis |last2=Silverstein |first2=Jason |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Omar Mateen's wife Noor Salman went with him to Pulse nightclub and to buy ammo, might face criminal charges |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/omar-mateen-wife-spotted-time-massacre-article-1.2672956 |work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]] |location=New York |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614122801/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/omar-mateen-wife-spotted-time-massacre-article-1.2672956 |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Motive===\nIn the hours before the shooting, Mateen used several [[Facebook]] accounts to write posts vowing vengeance for American airstrikes in Iraq and Syria and to search for content related to terrorism. These posts, since deleted, were recovered and included in an [[open letter]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/06/15/letter-from-sen-ron-johnson-to-facebook-regarding-orlando-shooters-posts.html |title=Letter from Sen. Ron Johnson to Facebook regarding Orlando shooter's posts |last=Johnson |first=Ron |date=June 15, 2016 |publisher=Fox News |access-date=July 2, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160620181712/http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/06/15/letter-from-sen-ron-johnson-to-facebook-regarding-orlando-shooters-posts.html |archivedate=June 20, 2016}}</ref> by Senate Homeland Security Chairman [[Ron Johnson (Wisconsin politician)|Ron Johnson]] to Facebook CEO [[Mark Zuckerberg]] seeking further information about Mateen's use of the site.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Blinder |first1=Alan |last2=Robles |first2=Frances |last3=P\u00e8rez-Pe\u00f1a |first3=Richard |date=June 16, 2016 |title=Omar Mateen Posted to Facebook Amid Orlando Attack, Lawmaker Says |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/17/us/orlando-shooting.html |work=The New York Time |access-date=June 18, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618111744/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/17/us/orlando-shooting.html |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Zimmerman |first=Malia |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Orlando terrorist's chilling Facebook posts from inside club revealed |url=http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/06/15/orlando-terrorists-chilling-facebook-posts-from-inside-club-revealed.html |publisher=Fox News |access-date=June 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616012540/http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/06/15/orlando-terrorists-chilling-facebook-posts-from-inside-club-revealed.html |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ross |first1=Brian |last2=Schwartz |first2=Rhonda |last3=Dukakis |first3=Alexandra |last4=Ferran |first4=Lee |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Orlando Shooter on Facebook: Now 'Taste' ISIS 'Vengeance' |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/orlando-shooter-facebook-now-taste-isis-vengeance/story?id=39875518 |publisher=ABC News |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616044519/http://abcnews.go.com/US/orlando-shooter-facebook-now-taste-isis-vengeance/story?id=39875518 |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nDuring the shooting, Mateen made a [[9-1-1]] call claiming it was an act of retaliation for the airstrike killing of, among others, ISIL militant [[Abu Waheeb]] in the previous month. He told the negotiator to tell America to stop the bombing.<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Reveal\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/09/28/transcripts-orlando-shooters-conversation-with-police-reveal-isis-influence.html |title=Transcripts of Orlando shooter's conversation with police reveal ISIS influence |work=FOX News |date=September 28, 2016 |accessdate=September 29, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160928185246/http://www.foxnews.com/us/2016/09/28/transcripts-orlando-shooters-conversation-with-police-reveal-isis-influence.html |archivedate=September 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAn unnamed police academy classmate said Mateen asked him out around 2006, that they had spent time at gay bars together after class, and that he believed Mateen was gay.<ref name=\"Sandoval13June\" /> He also described him as \"socially awkward\" and disliked by classmates.<ref name=\"classmate\">{{cite news |last=Mower |first=Lawrence |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Orlando shooter Omar Mateen was gay, former classmate says |url=http://www.palmbeachpost.com/news/news/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-was-gay-former-classma/nrfwW/ |newspaper=[[The Palm Beach Post]] |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614095038/http://www.palmbeachpost.com/news/news/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-was-gay-former-classma/nrfwW/ |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> A man who self-identified as Mateen's lover-of-two-months, \"Miguel\", stated that he believed the massacre was out of revenge against Latino men when Mateen learned he may have been exposed to [[HIV]] from a Puerto Rican man with whom he had sex.<ref name=\"FBINoEvidence\" /><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Omar Mateen's Alleged Male Lover Claims Orlando Nightclub Shooting Was Act Of 'Revenge' |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2016/06/22/omar-mateen-gay-lover-speaks/ |work=CBS New York |date=June 22, 2016 |access-date=July 1, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625160325/http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2016/06/22/omar-mateen-gay-lover-speaks/ |archivedate=June 25, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Omar Mateen's Alleged Male Lover: 'He Did It For Revenge' Against Latino Men |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2016/06/21/omar-mateen-gay-lover/ |work=CBS New York |date=June 21, 2016 |access-date=July 4, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160706174743/http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2016/06/21/omar-mateen-gay-lover/ |archivedate=July 6, 2016}}</ref> Mateen's autopsy results, however, showed that he was HIV-negative.<ref name=\"MateenAutopsy\" /> At least four regular Pulse customers reported having seen Mateen visit the nightclub on no fewer than a dozen occasions. One of them said he would sometimes become drunkenly \"loud and belligerent\", and at other times would drink in a corner by himself.<ref name=\"LotanBrinkmannStutzman\" /> According to a witness who recognized him outside the club an hour before the shooting, Mateen had messaged him using [[Jack'd]], a gay [[Mobile dating|dating app]], intermittently over the course of a year before the attack.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hennessy-Fiske |first1=Molly |last2=Jarvie |first2=Jenny |last3=Wilber |first3=Del Quentin |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Orlando gunman had used gay dating app and visited LGBT nightclub on other occasions, witnesses say |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-nightclub-shooting-20160613-snap-story.html |work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613233653/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-nightclub-shooting-20160613-snap-story.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> Another witness said Mateen used [[Grindr]], a gay hook-up app, and [[Adam4Adam]], a website to communicate with gay men, and had posted pictures of himself on both sites.<ref name=\"Sandoval13June\">{{cite news |last1=Sandoval |first1=Edgar |last2=Marcius |first2=Chelsia Rose |last3=Otis |first3=Ginger Adams |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Ex-classmate says Orlando shooter Omar Mateen was gay |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/orlando-shooter-reported-pulse-club-regular-patrons-article-1.2672445 |work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]] |location=New York |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614042049/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/orlando-shooter-reported-pulse-club-regular-patrons-article-1.2672445 |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> A third witness said Mateen would try to pick up men at the nightclub.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Pilkington |first1=Ed |last2=Elgot |first2=Jessica |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Orlando gunman Omar Mateen 'was a regular at Pulse nightclub' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/14/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-was-a-regular-at-nightclub |work=The Guardian |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614095531/http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/14/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-was-a-regular-at-nightclub |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\nHowever, according to federal law enforcement officials, the FBI suspects the witnesses claiming Mateen's [[homosexuality]] could be mistaken, and has doubts that Mateen was gay.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Blinder |first1=Alan |last2=Robles |first2=Frances |last3=P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |first3=Richard |date=June 16, 2016 |title=Omar Mateen Posted to Facebook Amid Orlando Attack, Lawmaker Says |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/17/us/orlando-shooting.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 18, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618111744/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/17/us/orlando-shooting.html |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"BullChris\">{{cite news |last=Bull |first=Chris |date=June 17, 2016 |title=FBI casts doubt on theory that Orlando shooter was secretly gay |url=http://www.lgbtqnation.com/2016/06/fbi-casts-doubt-theory-orlando-shooter-secretly-gay/ |publisher=LGBTQ Nation |access-date=June 18, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618155545/http://www.lgbtqnation.com/2016/06/fbi-casts-doubt-theory-orlando-shooter-secretly-gay/ |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref> Law enforcement sources said the FBI found no photographs, text messages, smartphone apps, pornography, or cell tower location data to suggest Mateen lived a gay life, [[closeted]] or otherwise.<ref name=\"FBINoEvidence\" /><ref name=\"FBI OM not gay\">{{cite news |last=Hennessy-Fiske |first=Molly |date=June 23, 2016 |title=FBI investigators say they have found no evidence that Orlando shooter had gay lovers |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-gay-fbi-20160623-snap-story.html |work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=June 25, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625004254/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-gay-fbi-20160623-snap-story.html |archivedate=June 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn the day of the shooting, Mateen's father, Mir Seddique Mateen, said that he had seen his son get angry after seeing a gay couple kiss in front of his family at the [[Bayside Marketplace]] in Miami months prior to the shooting, which he suggested might have been a motivating factor.<ref name=\"NBC.Shooting\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Hanks |first=Douglas |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Orlando shooter's father points to men kissing in Miami to explain son's anger |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/community/miami-dade/article83329252.html |work=Miami Herald |access-date=July 6, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160702083817/http://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/community/miami-dade/article83329252.html |archivedate=July 2, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Williams |first1=Pete |last2=Connor |first2=Tracy |last3=Ortiz |first3=Erik |last4=Gosk |first4=Stephanie |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Terror? Hate? What Motivated Orlando Nightclub Shooter? |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/terror-hate-what-motivated-orlando-nightclub-shooter-n590496 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612161631/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/terror-hate-what-motivated-orlando-nightclub-shooter-n590496 |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> Two days later, after his son's sexual orientation became a subject of speculation, Mateen's father said he did not believe his son was homosexual.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Orlando gunman's father reacts to speculation son was gay |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-shooting-gunman-omar-mateen-father-reacts-to-speculation-son-was-gay |publisher=CBS News |date=June 14, 2016 |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615124012/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-shooting-gunman-omar-mateen-father-reacts-to-speculation-son-was-gay/ |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> Mateen's ex-wife, however, claimed that his father called him gay while in her presence. Speaking on her behalf, her current fianc\u00e9 said that she, his family, and others believed he was gay, and that \"the FBI asked her not to tell this to the American media\".<ref name=\"NYPost\">{{cite news |last1=Perez |first1=Chris |last2=Tacopino |first2=Joe |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Ex-wife's bombshell claim: Club shooter was gay |url=https://nypost.com/2016/06/13/shooter-used-to-visit-orlando-gay-club-use-gay-dating-apps/ |work=New York Post |access-date=June 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616032218/http://nypost.com/2016/06/13/shooter-used-to-visit-orlando-gay-club-use-gay-dating-apps/ |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nDuring his wife's trial in March 2018, her defense revealed in a motion that Mateen had Googled \"downtown Orlando nightclubs\" and, after passing [[Disney Springs]], traveled between Pulse and the Eve Orlando Nightclub before choosing to target Pulse. Trial witnesses said the decision to target Pulse was made at the last minute,<ref>{{cite web |last=Speck |first=Emilee |url=https://www.clickorlando.com/news/noor-salman-trial/noor-salmans-lawyers-begin-presenting-defense-monday |title=Defense paints childlike picture of Noor Salman, reveals Pulse gunman's deception |work=ClickOrlando |date=March 26, 2018 |accessdate=March 27, 2018}}</ref> and the defense's motion argued that this \"strongly suggests that the attack on Pulse was not a result of a prior plan to attack a gay nightclub.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Greenwald |first=Glenn |url=https://theintercept.com/2018/03/05/as-the-trial-of-omar-mateens-wife-begins-new-evidence-undermines-beliefs-about-the-pulse-massacre-including-motive/ |title=As the Trial of Omar Mateen's Wife Begins, New Evidence Undermines Beliefs About the Pulse Massacre, Including Motive |date=March 5, 2018 |work=The Intercept |accessdate=March 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\n[[File:Washington DC Vigil for Orlando (27623767946).jpg|thumb|right|Vigil in [[Washington, D.C.]], {{nowrap|June 13}}, 2016|alt=Hundreds of people stand together listening to a man speaking from an outdoor stage. In the center of the crowd is a large statue with a paper sign affixed to it with tape; the sign reads: \"D.C. Loves You Orlando\".]]\n[[Security camera|Security-camera]] video footage was recovered from the nightclub as part of the investigation.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wilber |first1=Del Quentin |last2=Weiner |first2=Jeff |last3=Stutzman |first3=Rene |date=June 17, 2016 |title=Pulse nightclub security video recovered by agents |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/breaking-news/os-shooting-developments-friday-20160617-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618155525/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/breaking-news/os-shooting-developments-friday-20160617-story.html |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref> Facebook activated its \"[[Facebook Safety Check|Safety Check]]\" feature in the Orlando area following the shooting, allowing users to mark themselves as \"safe\" to notify family and friends\u2014the first use of the feature in the United States.<ref name=\"Shapiro\" /><ref name=\"Boggs\">{{cite news |last=Boggs |first=Justin |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Facebook activates Safety Check for Orlando residents |url=http://www.nbc26.com/news/national/facebook-activates-safety-check-for-orlando-residents |publisher=[[WGBA-TV]] |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160620232318/http://www.nbc26.com/news/national/facebook-activates-safety-check-for-orlando-residents |archivedate=June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the shooting, many business venues in the United States, such as shopping malls, movie theaters, bars, and concert halls, reexamined their security procedures.<ref name=\"HalzackHuiO'Connell\">{{cite news |last1=Halzack |first1=Sarah |last2=Hui |first2=Mary |last3=O'Connell |first3=Jonathan |date=June 13, 2016 |title=In wake of Orlando attack, venues across country revisit security |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/economy/in-wake-of-orlando-attack-venues-across-country-revisit-security/2016/06/13/04af3ae4-3191-11e6-8ff7-7b6c1998b7a0_story.html |work=The Washington Post |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614023307/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/economy/in-wake-of-orlando-attack-venues-across-country-revisit-security/2016/06/13/04af3ae4-3191-11e6-8ff7-7b6c1998b7a0_story.html |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Cherney |first=Elyssa |date=July 26, 2016 |title=Orlando nightclub task force meets for first time since Pulse shooting |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-nightclub-task-force-meeting-20160726-story.html |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 27, 2016 |quote=But after the mass shooting at Pulse last month, the group's [Nightclub Task Force's] focus is shifting to include a look at best security measures to keep guns out of the packed establishments. The task force, composed of the city's downtown development board and club owners, met on Tuesday [July 26] for the first time since the June 12 massacre. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728162213/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-nightclub-task-force-meeting-20160726-story.html |archivedate=July 28, 2016}}</ref> Also, police forces across the country announced plans to increase security at LGBT landmarks such as the [[Stonewall Inn]] and at [[Pride Month]] events including [[pride parade]]s.<ref>{{cite news |last=Domonoske |first=Camila |date=June 12, 2016 |title=LGBT Community Mourns Orlando Attack, Boosts Security at Pride Events |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/06/12/481793981/lgbt-community-mourns-orlando-attack-boosts-security-at-pride-events |publisher=NPR |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613234622/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/06/12/481793981/lgbt-community-mourns-orlando-attack-boosts-security-at-pride-events |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nTwo former SWAT members, one an active-shooter tactics expert and trainer, expressed misgivings about the three-hour delay in breaching the nightclub, citing the lesson learned from other mass shootings that officers can minimize casualties only by entering a shooting location expeditiously, even if it means putting themselves at great risk.<ref>{{cite news |last=Pane |first=Lisa Marie |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Delayed police response in Florida shooting questioned |url=http://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/nation/2016/06/13/orlando-shooting-police-response/85834624/ |work=The Detroit News |agency=Associated Press |access-date=June 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617074310/http://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/nation/2016/06/13/orlando-shooting-police-response/85834624/ |archivedate=June 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\nSeddique Mateen released a [[Dari language]] video statement via Facebook on {{nowrap|June 13}} to speak about his son's actions.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Craig |first1=Tim |last2=Bearak |first2=Max |last3=Powell |first3=Lee |date=June 13, 2016 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the-orlando-shooters-afghan-roots/2016/06/13/d89a8cd0-30e4-11e6-ab9d-1da2b0f24f93_story.html |title=Shooter Omar Mateen's father says he's saddened by massacre, calls gunman 'a good son' |newspaper=The Washington Post |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613123403/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the-orlando-shooters-afghan-roots/2016/06/13/d89a8cd0-30e4-11e6-ab9d-1da2b0f24f93_story.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Tamplin |first=Harley |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Orlando gunman's dad says God should have punished gays, not his son |url=http://metro.co.uk/2016/06/13/orlando-gunmans-dad-said-he-shouldnt-have-killed-gays-because-god-will-punish-them-instead-5941213/ |newspaper=Metro |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614045318/http://metro.co.uk/2016/06/13/orlando-gunmans-dad-said-he-shouldnt-have-killed-gays-because-god-will-punish-them-instead-5941213/ |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\nA {{nowrap|June 13}} broadcast from the Iraqi ISIL radio station [[Al-Bayan (radio station)|al-Bayan]] said Mateen was \"one of the soldiers of the caliphate in America\", without indicating any foreknowledge of the shooting.<ref name=\"Stoffel\" />\n\nOn {{nowrap|September 10}}, the [[Florida Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services]] fined [[G4S Secure Solutions]] $151,400 for providing inaccurate psychological testing information on more than 1,500 forms over a ten-year period, which allowed employees to carry firearms. Mateen's form was among those investigated.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/security-firm-employed-orlando-club-killer-fined-inaccurate-202827699.html |title=Security firm that employed Orlando club killer fined for inaccurate forms |work=Yahoo! News |date=September 10, 2016 |accessdate=September 10, 2016 |first=Ben |last=Klayman |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911154834/https://www.yahoo.com/news/security-firm-employed-orlando-club-killer-fined-inaccurate-202827699.html |archivedate=September 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn {{nowrap|November 4}}, it was reported that the Orlando Police Department was upgrading its equipment for officers following the shooting, since officers at the nightclub were not well-equipped for the event and therefore endangered. The upgraded equipment included bulletproof helmets and heavier bulletproof vests.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wftv.com/news/9-investigates/orlando-police-upgrades-equipment-following-pulse-mass-shooting/464055241 |title=Orlando police upgrades equipment following Pulse mass shooting |work=WFTV |date=November 4, 2016 |accessdate=November 6, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105135449/http://www.wftv.com/news/9-investigates/orlando-police-upgrades-equipment-following-pulse-mass-shooting/464055241 |archivedate=November 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the shooting and [[Ohio State University attack|a vehicle-ramming attack and mass stabbing]] at [[Ohio State University]] in [[Columbus, Ohio]], a new federal initiative was launched, partially in response to at least one victim bleeding to death inside Pulse during the shooting. The initiative was designed to train people working at schools and other public places on how to treat injuries before paramedics arrive at the scene. Doctors have emphasized the importance for school faculty members to stay calm and assess injuries, but also discouraged the use of more invasive emergency procedures such as removing a bullet.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/ohio-state-university-attack-need-training-ordinary-people-save-lives/ |title=Ohio State University attack highlights need for training ordinary people to save lives |publisher=CBS News |agency=Associated Press |date=November 30, 2016 |accessdate=November 30, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201140127/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/ohio-state-university-attack-need-training-ordinary-people-save-lives/ |archivedate=December 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Victim assistance efforts===\nThe FBI's Office of Victim Assistance (OVA) provided \"information, assistance services, and resources\" to the victims and witnesses of the shooting that, depending on their case-by-case eligibility, may have consisted of \"special funding to provide emergency assistance, crime victim compensation, and counseling\".<ref name=\"G-MenAgency\" /> The OVA, through its Victim Assistance Rapid Deployment Team and Crisis Response Canines, also provided help to responders of the shooting in the days following {{nowrap|June 12}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fbi.gov/audio-repository/ftw-comey-on-orlando-mp3-for-audio-podcasting.mp3/view |title=FBI Provides Assistance to Pulse Nightclub Shooting Victims |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=June 15, 2016 |website=Federal Bureau of Investigation |access-date=July 23, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816075002/https://www.fbi.gov/audio-repository/ftw-comey-on-orlando-mp3-for-audio-podcasting.mp3/view |archivedate=August 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nImmediately after the shooting, many people lined up to [[donate blood]] at local [[List of blood donation agencies in the United States|blood donation centers]] and [[bloodmobile]] locations when OneBlood, a regional blood donation agency, urged people to donate.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hudak |first=Stephen |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Blood donors needed after mass shooting in Orlando |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/breaking-news/os-orlando-nightclub-shooting-blood-donations-20160612-story.html |work=[[Orlando Sentinel]] |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612152010/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/breaking-news/os-orlando-nightclub-shooting-blood-donations-20160612-story.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Urgent Need For Blood After Mass Shooting |url=https://www.oneblood.org/media/press-releases/urgent-need-for-blood-after-mass-shooting.stml |publisher=OneBlood |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823172127/https://www.oneblood.org/media/press-releases/urgent-need-for-blood-after-mass-shooting.stml |archivedate=August 23, 2016}}</ref> The surge in blood donations and the fact that the shooting targeted a gay nightclub spotlighted the [[Food and Drug Administration]]'s [[Men who have sex with men blood donor controversy|controversial federal policy]] that forbids [[Men who have sex with men|men who had sex with men]] in the past year from donating blood. Despite expressions of frustration and disapproval by a number of gay and bisexual men, and LGBT activists across the country and a group of [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] lawmakers<ref>{{cite news |last=Barron-Lopez |first=Laura |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Democrats Call On FDA To End Ban On Blood Donations From Gay Men |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/democrats-blood-donations-gay_us_575ed49ce4b0ced23ca8b4b3 |work=The Huffington Post |access-date=July 31, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160813164107/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/democrats-blood-donations-gay_us_575ed49ce4b0ced23ca8b4b3 |archivedate=August 13, 2016}}</ref> urging the ban to be lifted, FDA stated on {{nowrap|June 14}} that it had no plans to change the regulation and will reevaluate its policies \"as new scientific information becomes available\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Levin |first=Sam |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Activists urge US to end ban on gay men donating blood after Orlando massacre |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/14/orlando-pulse-shooting-gay-blood-ban-lgbt-rights |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=June 15, 2016 |quote='The FDA has examined the possibility of eliminating all deferrals for HIV and simply relying on testing of donated blood or reducing the deferral window; however, scientifically robust data are not available to show that this would not lead to decreased safety of the blood supply,' the agency said in a statement to the Guardian. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615024250/http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/14/orlando-pulse-shooting-gay-blood-ban-lgbt-rights |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Margolin |first=Emma |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Blood Donations Skyrocket, but Gay Men Left Out |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/blood-donations-skyrocket-gay-men-left-out-n592656 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615131239/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/blood-donations-skyrocket-gay-men-left-out-n592656 |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=McKenzie |first=Sheena |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Gay men outraged over continued ban on blood donation |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/13/health/orlando-shooting-gay-men-donate-blood/ |work=CNN |access-date=July 11, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719130651/http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/13/health/orlando-shooting-gay-men-donate-blood/ |archivedate=July 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\nA victims' assistance center, Orlando Family Assistance Center, was opened on {{nowrap|June 15}} inside [[Camping World Stadium]] by the City of Orlando.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Weiner |first1=Jeff |last2=Hayes |first2=Christal |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Orlando setting up assistance center at Camping World Stadium |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-nightclub-shooting-assistance-center-20160614-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 5, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707053438/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-nightclub-shooting-assistance-center-20160614-story.html |archivedate=July 7, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Hume |first=Jerry |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Family assistance center opens for Pulse victims, family |url=http://www.baynews9.com/content/news/baynews9/news/article.html/content/news/articles/cfn/2016/6/15/family_assistance_ce.html |work=Bay News 9 |access-date=July 26, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160720143547/http://www.baynews9.com/content/news/baynews9/news/article.html/content/news/articles/cfn/2016/6/15/family_assistance_ce.html |archivedate=July 20, 2016}}</ref> During the eight days it was open, it provided help to 956 people from 298 families. Those remaining were then directed to the newly opened Orlando United Assistance Center jointly set up by the City and [[Orange County, Florida|Orange County]], which, according to the mayor of Orlando, \"will stay open as long as there is a need\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Castro |first1=Amanda |last2=Winningham |first2=Cathleigh |date=June 23, 2016 |title=New Orlando United Assistance Center for Pulse Nightclub victims opens |url=http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/new-united-assistance-center-for-pulse-nightclub-victims-opens-thursday |work=News 6 WKMG ClickOrlando |access-date=July 26, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160811193855/http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/new-united-assistance-center-for-pulse-nightclub-victims-opens-thursday |archivedate=August 11, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Weiner |first=Jeff |date=June 23, 2016 |title=Dyer, Jacobs open Orlando United Assistance Center |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-united-assistance-center-pulse-20160623-story.html |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 26, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160727150748/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-orlando-united-assistance-center-pulse-20160623-story.html |archivedate=July 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe two hospitals that treated Pulse victims, Orlando Regional Medical Center and Florida Hospital, announced in late August that they will not be billing the survivors or pursuing reimbursement.<ref>{{cite news |last=Caplan |first=David |date=August 25, 2016 |title=Orlando Hospitals Won't Bill Pulse Nightclub Massacre Victims |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/orlando-hospitals-bill-pulse-nightclub-massacre-victims/story?id=41639209 |publisher=ABC News |access-date=August 25, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825102335/http://abcnews.go.com/US/orlando-hospitals-bill-pulse-nightclub-massacre-victims/story?id=41639209 |archivedate=August 25, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Two Orlando hospitals won't bill survivors of Pulse nightclub shooting |url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/health/medicine/two-orlando-hospitals-wont-bill-nightclub-shooting-victims/2290897 |work=Tampa Bay Times |date=August 25, 2016 |access-date=August 25, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826192100/http://www.tampabay.com/news/health/medicine/two-orlando-hospitals-wont-bill-nightclub-shooting-victims/2290897 |archivedate=August 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe City of Orlando offered free plots and funeral service at the city-owned [[Greenwood Cemetery (Orlando, Florida)|Greenwood Cemetery]] for those killed in the shooting.<ref>{{cite news |first=Jeff |last=Weiner |title=Orlando to give Pulse victims Greenwood Cemetery plots |date=June 13, 2016 |accessdate=August 26, 2016 |website=Orlando Sentinel |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/breaking-news/os-orlando-mass-shooting-greenwood-cemetery-20160613-story.html |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160908010730/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/breaking-news/os-orlando-mass-shooting-greenwood-cemetery-20160613-story.html |archivedate=September 8, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Free Cemetery Plots for Orlando Shooting Victims |url=http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/national-international/Free-Cemetery-Plots-for-Orlando-Shooting-Victims-383623431.html |work=WESH |publisher=NBC 4 New York |date=June 20, 2016 |access-date=August 26, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827233336/http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/national-international/Free-Cemetery-Plots-for-Orlando-Shooting-Victims-383623431.html |archivedate=August 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Cemetery donates land to Orlando shooting victims |url=http://www.clickorlando.com/news/cemetery-donates-land-to-orlando-shooting-victims |publisher=News 6 ClickOrlando |agency=Associated Press |date=June 14, 2016 |access-date=August 26, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827181308/http://www.clickorlando.com/news/cemetery-donates-land-to-orlando-shooting-victims |archivedate=August 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Fundraising campaigns===\n[[Equality Florida]], the state's largest [[LGBT rights]] group, started a fundraising page to aid the victims and their families, raising $767,000 in the first nine hours.<ref name=\"Shapiro\">{{cite news |last=Shapiro |first=Julie |date=June 12, 2016 |title=How to Help the Victims of the Pulse Orlando Nightclub Shooting |url=http://time.com/4365295/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-victims-help/ |work=Time |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612172459/http://time.com/4365295/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-victims-help/ |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"cnnwire\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s) of CNN Wire; no by-line--> |title=GoFundMe campaign raises $767K in 9 hours for Pulse shooting victims |url=http://wtvr.com/2016/06/12/gofundme-campaign-raises-767k-in-9-hours-for-pulse-shooting-victims/ |publisher=WTVR |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613154111/http://wtvr.com/2016/06/12/gofundme-campaign-raises-767k-in-9-hours-for-pulse-shooting-victims/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Wattles |first1=Jackie |last2=Chillag |first2=Amy |date=June 12, 2016 |title=GoFundMe campaign raises more than $1 million for Pulse shooting victims |url=http://money.cnn.com/2016/06/12/news/gofundme-orlando-pulse-shooting/index.html |publisher=CNN |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613020828/http://money.cnn.com/2016/06/12/news/gofundme-orlando-pulse-shooting/index.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> As of {{nowrap|September 22}}, 2016, they have raised over $7.85 million online, a record for [[GoFundMe]], with a total of over 119,400 donors and an average of about $66 per donation.<ref>{{cite news |last=Maxwell |first=Dani |date=June 13, 2016 |title=GoFundMe page set up for Orlando's Pulse Nightclub shooting victims |url=http://www.wkow.com/story/32205361/2016/06/13/gofundme-page-set-up-for-orlandos-pulse-nightclub-shooting-victims |publisher=WKOW |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616123558/http://www.wkow.com/story/32205361/2016/06/13/gofundme-page-set-up-for-orlandos-pulse-nightclub-shooting-victims |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Kraft\">{{cite news |last=Kraft |first=Ann |date=June 14, 2016 |title=GoFundMe raises over $3 million for Orlando shooting victims |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-shooting-gofundme-raises-money-for-pulse-nightclub-victims/ |publisher=[[CBS News]] |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614100424/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-shooting-gofundme-raises-money-for-pulse-nightclub-victims/ |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Wattles\">{{cite news |last1=Wattles |first1=Jackie |last2=Chillag |first2=Amy |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Orlando GoFundMe campaign sets record |url=http://money.cnn.com/2016/06/14/technology/gofundme-orlando-pulse-shooting/ |work=[[CNN Money]] |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615111524/http://money.cnn.com/2016/06/14/technology/gofundme-orlando-pulse-shooting/ |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAnother fundraising campaign, OneOrlando, was established by Mayor [[Buddy Dyer]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cityoforlando.net/mayor/2016/06/the-oneorlando-fund/ |title=The OneOrlando Fund |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=June 14, 2016 |website=City of Orlando |access-date=July 2, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160630041825/http://www.cityoforlando.net/mayor/2016/06/the-oneorlando-fund/ |archivedate=June 30, 2016}}</ref> [[The Walt Disney Company]] and [[NBCUniversal]], which operate the nearby [[Walt Disney World Resort]] and [[Universal Orlando Resort]], respectively, each donated $1 million to the fund.<ref>{{cite news |last=Rainey |first=James |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Disney Donates $1 Million to Orlando Shooting Victims |url=https://variety.com/2016/biz/news/disney-donates-1-million-to-orlando-shooting-victims-1201795387/#article-comments |work=Variety |access-date=June 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615152832/http://variety.com/2016/biz/news/disney-donates-1-million-to-orlando-shooting-victims-1201795387/#article-comments |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Pedicini |first1=Sandra |date=June 16, 2016 |title=Universal Orlando owner donating $1 million to help after Pulse shooting |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-comcast-universal-oneorlando-20160616-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=June 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617150909/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-comcast-universal-oneorlando-20160616-story.html |archivedate=June 17, 2016}}</ref> As of {{nowrap|August 12}}, OneOrlando has raised $23 million,<ref name=\"OneOrlandoRules\" /> with a draft proposal to start payouts starting {{nowrap|September 27}} on a rolling basis in which the highest compensations will go to the families of the 49 people killed, followed by the 50 victims who were physically injured and hospitalized for one night or more. OneOrlando's fund administrator said that the draft has not decided whether to pay people who were held hostage but were not injured, and will take public feedback in two 90-minute hearings to be held on {{nowrap|August 4}}. A timeline of the draft proposal was released.<ref>{{cite news |last=Knothe |first=Ali |date=July 14, 2016 |title=Proposal details how $20 million fund for Pulse nightclub shooting victims would be distributed |url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/publicsafety/crime/proposal-details-how-fund-for-pulse-nightclub-shooting-victims-would-be/2285400 |newspaper=Tampa Bay Times |access-date=July 17, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160715142709/http://www.tampabay.com/news/publicsafety/crime/proposal-details-how-fund-for-pulse-nightclub-shooting-victims-would-be/2285400 |archivedate=July 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Timeline of how OneOrlando money will be distributed to victims, survivors |url=http://www.wftv.com/news/pulse-shooting/timeline-of-how-oneorlando-money-will-be-distributed-to-victims-survivors/400928988 |work=WFTV 9 ABC |publisher=Cox Media Group |date=July 14, 2016 |access-date=July 17, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160715151106/http://www.wftv.com/news/pulse-shooting/timeline-of-how-oneorlando-money-will-be-distributed-to-victims-survivors/400928988 |archivedate=July 15, 2016}}</ref> On {{nowrap|August 11}}, its board of directors decided that the funds will only be dispersed to \"the families of the dead, survivors who were hospitalized, survivors who sought outpatient medical treatment, and those who were present in the club when the shootings began but not physically injured\", and that family members and survivors can start filing claims until the {{nowrap|September 12}} deadline.<ref name=\"OneOrlandoRules\">{{cite news |last=Santich |first=Kate |date=August 12, 2016 |title=OneOrlando Fund sets final rules on who gets money |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-one-orlando-fund-final-20160811-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=August 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160813140616/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-one-orlando-fund-final-20160811-story.html |archivedate=August 13, 2016}}</ref> As of {{nowrap|December 1}}, OneOrlando paid out over $27.4 million to 299 recipients, according to officials, with six more claims worth an additional $2.1 million still being contested among family members of the slain victims.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-one-orlando-final-payouts-20161201-story.html |title=OneOrlando Fund has paid out $27M. What have Pulse victims done with their share? |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=December 1, 2016 |accessdate=December 2, 2016 |first1=Christal |last1=Hayes |first2=Kate |last2=Santich |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161203123555/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-one-orlando-final-payouts-20161201-story.html |archivedate=December 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[IDW Publishing]] and [[DC Entertainment]] created [[Love Is Love (comics)|LOVE IS LOVE]], a graphic novel sold to raise money for the victims. The novel became a New York Time's best seller and more than $165,000 was raised. Through [[Equality Florida]], the proceeds were donated to the OneOrlando Fund.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newsarama.com/33772-idw-dc-s-love-is-love-raises-165k-for-charity-gets-5th-printing.html |title=IDW & DC's LOVE IS LOVE Raises $165k For Charity, Gets 5th Printing |work=Newsarama|access-date=April 27, 2017 |language=en |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170428142514/http://www.newsarama.com/33772-idw-dc-s-love-is-love-raises-165k-for-charity-gets-5th-printing.html |archivedate=April 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Release of transcripts and videos===\nA total of 603 calls to 9-1-1 were made by victims, family members and friends of victims, bystanders, and rescue workers during the entire shooting.<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Flood\">{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-full-911-call-release-20160909-story.html |title=Newly released files show flood of Pulse calls to 911 operators |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=September 14, 2016 |accessdate=September 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160915150531/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-full-911-call-release-20160909-story.html |archivedate=September 15, 2016}}</ref> On {{nowrap|June 14}}, two dozen news agencies sent a four-page letter to Orlando's city attorney jointly demanding the release of recordings that 9-1-1 callers made on the night of the shooting. The letter also contained a request for scanner and dispatch recordings. The Orlando police refused to release the recordings, citing an \"ongoing investigation\".<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |date=June 16, 2016 |title=Orlando terror attack updates: Obama meets with victims' families in Orlando |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-nightclub-shooting-live-media-push-for-release-of-911-tapes-in-1465960629-htmlstory.html |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618100732/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-orlando-nightclub-shooting-live-media-push-for-release-of-911-tapes-in-1465960629-htmlstory.html |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Alanez |first=Tonya |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Media jointly demand release of Orlando shooting 911 calls |url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/fl-media-lawyers-seek-orlando-911-recordings-20160614-story.html |work=Sun-Sentinel |access-date=July 26, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160731003407/http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/fl-media-lawyers-seek-orlando-911-recordings-20160614-story.html |archivedate=July 31, 2016}}</ref> {{nowrap|June 20}}, the FBI released a transcript of the first call by the shooter and a summary of three calls with police negotiators.<ref name=\"fbitranscript\" /> On {{nowrap|July 14}}, the [[University of Central Florida Police Department]] released nine [[body camera]] videos of UCFPD officers who rushed to Pulse to help Orlando police officers during the incident.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=UCFPD releases body camera video in Pulse nightclub shooting |url=http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/ucfpd-releases-body-camera-video-in-pulse-nightclub-shooting |publisher=WKMG ClickOrlando |date=July 14, 2016 |access-date=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160718014225/http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/ucfpd-releases-body-camera-video-in-pulse-nightclub-shooting |archivedate=July 18, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn {{nowrap|July 18}}, the City of Orlando released a detailed 71-page document of OPD officers' accounts and responses to the shooting. Requests to release recordings of 9-1-1 calls, police radio transmissions, and the exchanges between law enforcement and Mateen were denied, citing disagreements over whether they fall under local or federal jurisdiction. The status on the authority over the recordings is pending a court ruling.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lotan |first=Gal Tziperman |date=July 19, 2016 |title=Orlando police officers detail harrowing response to Pulse shooting |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-orlando-police-narrative-20160719-story.html |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160720181634/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-orlando-police-narrative-20160719-story.html |archivedate=July 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=New police reports released detail Orlando nightclub shooting |url=http://www.wkbw.com/news/us-news-world/new-police-reports-released-detail-orlando-nightclub-shooting |publisher=WKBW |agency=Associated Press |date=July 19, 2016 |access-date=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160720225831/http://www.wkbw.com/news/us-news-world/new-police-reports-released-detail-orlando-nightclub-shooting |archivedate=July 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ansari |first1=Azadeh |last2=Stapleton |first2=AnneClaire<!--One word name; no hyphen.--> |date=July 19, 2016 |title=Pulse nightclub shooting details revealed in police report |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/19/us/orlando-pulse-nightclub-officer-accounts/ |work=CNN |access-date=July 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160720165626/http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/19/us/orlando-pulse-nightclub-officer-accounts/ |archivedate=July 20, 2016}}</ref> On {{nowrap|July 20}}, the Orange County Sheriff's Office (OCSO) released video footage from a body camera worn by one of its deputies during the incident.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Deputy's body camera gives glimpse of Orlando nightclub shooting |url=http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/ocso-releases-pulse-body-cam-video- |work=News 6 |publisher=WKMG ClickOrlando |publication-date=July 20, 2016 |date=July 21, 2016 |access-date=July 21, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160724010211/http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/ocso-releases-pulse-body-cam-video- |archivedate=July 24, 2016}}</ref> On {{nowrap|July 26}}, the [[Orange County Fire Rescue]] released a recording of a 9-1-1 call made during the shooting.<ref>{{cite news |last=Doornbos |first=Caitlin |date=July 26, 2016 |title=Orange County Fire Rescue releases Pulse 911 call |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-orange-fire-911-20160726-story.html |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 26, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160727134336/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-orange-fire-911-20160726-story.html |archivedate=July 27, 2016}}</ref> On {{nowrap|July 29}}, the OCSO released dozens of pages<!--Fox 35 News says 98 pages; Orlando Sentinel says 60. 60+21(see OCSO PDF in External Links)\u226098.--> of documents detailing the deputies' individual accounts of their involvement in the shooting.<ref>{{cite news |last=Delgado |first=Kirstin |date=July 29, 2016 |title=Orange County Sheriff releases new batch of documents from Pulse shooting |url=http://www.fox35orlando.com/news/local-news/183441873-story |publisher=Fox 35 News |access-date=July 30, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160731193443/http://www.fox35orlando.com/news/local-news/183441873-story |archivedate=July 31, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"OCSOdocs\">{{cite news |last=Hayes |first=Christal |date=July 29, 2016 |title=150 shots fired in gunbattle with Pulse killer, records show |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-orange-county-reports-20160729-story.html |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 30, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160730202749/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-orange-county-reports-20160729-story.html |archivedate=July 30, 2016}}</ref> On {{nowrap|August 30}}, the OCSO released the 9-1-1 calls it received during the shooting.<ref name=\"OCSO911ABC\">{{cite news |last1=Margolin |first1=Josh |last2=Shapiro |first2=Emily |date=August 30, 2016 |title=911 Calls From Pulse Nightclub Shooting Released |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/911-calls-pulse-nightclub-shooting-released/story?id=41742808 |work=ABC News |access-date=August 30, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831031954/http://abcnews.go.com/US/911-calls-pulse-nightclub-shooting-released/story?id=41742808 |archivedate=August 31, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"OCSO911CNN\">{{cite news |last1=McLaughlin |first1=Eliott C. |last2=Shah |first2=Khushbu |date=August 30, 2016 |title=Orlando Pulse 911 caller: 'Gunshots were just going like crazy' |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/08/30/us/orlando-pulse-nightclub-shooting-911-calls/ |work=CNN |access-date=August 30, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831152434/http://www.cnn.com/2016/08/30/us/orlando-pulse-nightclub-shooting-911-calls/ |archivedate=August 31, 2016}}</ref> Two days later, OPD and the city of Orlando released nine of their hundreds of 9-1-1 calls, which were all made by friends and relatives outside of Pulse during the incident; the rest are locked in a legal dispute between 24 media groups, OPD, and the city of Orlando.<ref>{{cite news |last=Eversley |first=Melanie |date=September 1, 2016 |title=Orlando releases 911 tapes from Pulse nightclub shooting |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/09/01/orlando-releases-911-tapes-pulse-nightclub-shooting/89743146/ |work=USA Today |access-date=September 2, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160905090107/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/09/01/orlando-releases-911-tapes-pulse-nightclub-shooting/89743146/ |archivedate=September 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Couwels |first1=John |last2=Grinberg |first2=Emanuella |date=September 1, 2016 |title=Pulse 911 calls from Orlando police released |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/09/01/us/orlando-pulse-shooting-911-calls/ |work=CNN |access-date=September 2, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160903174044/http://www.cnn.com/2016/09/01/us/orlando-pulse-shooting-911-calls/ |archivedate=September 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Schneider |first=Mike |date=September 2, 2016 |title=Orlando releases nine out of the hundreds of 911 Pulse calls |url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/nation/orlando-releases-9-of-the-hundreds-of-911-pulse-calls/2292002 |newspaper=Tampa Bay Times |agency=Associated Press |access-date=September 2, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160903173902/http://www.tampabay.com/news/nation/orlando-releases-9-of-the-hundreds-of-911-pulse-calls/2292002 |archivedate=September 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Justice Dept. Wants Pulse 911 Case Kept In Federal Court |url=http://miami.cbslocal.com/2016/09/02/justice-dept-wants-pulse-911-case-kept-in-federal-court/ |publisher=CBS Miami |date=September 2, 2016 |access-date=September 2, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160903140252/http://miami.cbslocal.com/2016/09/02/justice-dept-wants-pulse-911-case-kept-in-federal-court/ |archivedate=September 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn {{nowrap|September 14}}, the city of Orlando released 23 additional 9-1-1 calls made during the shooting.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/09/14/orlando-releases-more-9-1-1-tapes-related-pulse-shooting/90392688/ |title=Orlando releases more 9-1-1 tapes related to Pulse shooting |work=USA Today |date=September 14, 2016 |accessdate=September 14, 2016 |first=Melanie |last=Eversley |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919112327/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2016/09/14/orlando-releases-more-9-1-1-tapes-related-pulse-shooting/90392688/ |archivedate=September 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.clickorlando.com/news/more-911-calls-released-in-pulse-nightclub-shooting |title=More 911 calls released in Pulse nightclub shooting |work=WKMG Orlando |date=September 14, 2016 |accessdate=September 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160915182004/http://www.clickorlando.com/news/more-911-calls-released-in-pulse-nightclub-shooting |archivedate=September 15, 2016}}</ref> These included calls made from rescue workers advising preparedness for dozens of victims,<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Flood\"/> a patron who escaped from Pulse with a friend who was shot, and the brother of a woman who was shot several times and trapped inside a bathroom in the nightclub.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/orlando-releases-911-calls-gay-nightclub-shooting-42101005|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160915193629/http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/orlando-releases-911-calls-gay-nightclub-shooting-42101005|url-status=dead|archive-date=September 15, 2016 |title=Orlando Releases More 911 Calls From Gay Nightclub Shooting |publisher=ABC News |agency=Associated Press |date=September 14, 2016 |accessdate=September 14, 2016 |first=Mike |last=Schneider}}</ref> On {{nowrap|October 31}}, the City of Orlando released nearly 30 minutes of recordings of police negotiators talking with Mateen during the course of the shooting, after a judge with the [[Ninth Judicial Circuit Court of Florida]] ruled that these calls should be made public. A total of 232 other calls are still being withheld by the city.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/audio-captures-police-strategizing-nightclub-shooter-085816511.html?ref=gs |title=Audio captures police strategizing about nightclub shooter |work=Yahoo! News |agency=Associated Press |date=November 1, 2016 |accessdate=November 1, 2016 |first=Mike |last=Schneider |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103234309/https://www.yahoo.com/news/audio-captures-police-strategizing-nightclub-shooter-085816511.html?ref=gs |archivedate=November 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-omar-mateen-pulse-911-calls-20161031-story.html |title=Audio of Omar Mateen's 911 calls during Pulse massacre released |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=October 31, 2016 |accessdate=November 1, 2016 |first1=Gal Tziperman |last1=Lotan |first2=Rene |last2=Stutzman |first3=David |last3=Harris |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101014635/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-omar-mateen-pulse-911-calls-20161031-story.html |archivedate=November 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn {{nowrap|November 10}}, the Orange County Sheriff's office released about two dozen videos of [[body camera]] footage of officers at the perimeter of the nightclub during the shooting. The footage, which was heavily censored, depicted officers conducting searches of bathrooms in the nightclub and tending to survivors.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/body-cam-video-shows-deputies-responding-orlando-nightclub/story?id=43450952 |title=Body Cam Video Shows Deputies Responding to Orlando Nightclub Shooting |work=ABC News |date=November 10, 2016 |accessdate=November 12, 2016 |first1=Aaron |last1=Katersky |first2=Josh |last2=Margolin |first3=Emily |last3=Shapiro |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111112708/http://abcnews.go.com/US/body-cam-video-shows-deputies-responding-orlando-nightclub/story?id=43450952 |archivedate=November 11, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-ocso-bodycam-20161110-story.html |title=Deputies release body cam footage from inside Pulse |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=November 10, 2016 |accessdate=November 12, 2016 |first1=Christal |last1=Hayes |first2=David |last2=Harris |first3=Gal Tziperman |last3=Lotan |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111233134/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-ocso-bodycam-20161110-story.html |archivedate=November 11, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/crime/article114251728.html |title='Dude, that was a massacre': Body cameras show deputies responding to Pulse shooting |work=Miami Herald |date=November 11, 2016 |accessdate=November 12, 2016 |first=Alex |last=Harris |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111234357/http://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/crime/article114251728.html |archivedate=November 11, 2016}}</ref> On {{nowrap|November 14}}, the City of Orlando released 36 police audio recordings made during the shooting, which record officers' attempts to contact Mateen, their remarks on his \"serious, unruffled attitude\", and their conversations about how to respond to the hostage situation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-releases-new-batch-of-calls-in-pulse-nightclub-shooting-1479168155 |title=Orlando Releases New Batch of Calls in Pulse Nightclub Shooting |work=The Wall Street Journal |date=November 14, 2016 |accessdate=November 14, 2016 |first1=Jon |last1=Kamp |first2=Arian |last2=Campo-Flores |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115002404/http://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-releases-new-batch-of-calls-in-pulse-nightclub-shooting-1479168155 |archivedate=November 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/breaking-news/os-pulse-911-calls-released-20161114-story.html |title=Newly released Pulse 911 calls reveal terror, panic during, after shooting |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=November 14, 2016 |accessdate=November 14, 2016 |first1=Rene |last1=Stutzman |first2=Susan |last2=Jacobson |first3=Gal Tziperman |last3=Lotan |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114220449/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/breaking-news/os-pulse-911-calls-released-20161114-story.html |archivedate=November 14, 2016}}</ref> Also released that day was an additional 9-1-1 call made by a woman who made it out of the nightclub with her sister, who was shot.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/first-batch-of-pulse-shooting-calls-released-after-court-order |title=First batch of Pulse shooting calls released after court order |work=WKMG Orlando |date=November 14, 2016 |accessdate=November 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115193521/http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/first-batch-of-pulse-shooting-calls-released-after-court-order |archivedate=November 15, 2016}}</ref> The next day, on {{nowrap|November 15}}, 21 additional 9-1-1 calls were released.<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Question\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-more-pulse-911-calls-released-20170101-story.html |title=Pulse 911 calls reveal terror inside club |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=November 15, 2016 |accessdate=November 16, 2016 |first1=Charles |last1=Minshew |first2=Gal Tziperman |last2=Lotan |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116144906/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-more-pulse-911-calls-released-20170101-story.html |archivedate=November 16, 2016}}</ref> This was followed by three additional hours of 9-1-1 calls released on {{nowrap|November 16}}. In many of these calls, people who were trapped inside bathrooms, kitchens, and an upstairs office were questioning why police had yet to enter the nightclub.<ref name=\"OrlandoSentinel.Question\"/> Two days later, on {{nowrap|November 18}}, 107 pages of transcripts of more than 30 9-1-1 calls were released. These calls were made during the first ten minutes of the shooting, and had to be released in the form of transcripts after a judge deemed them too graphic to be released as audio recordings. According to a city spokesman, all 9-1-1 calls made during the shooting have now been released to the public.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-911-calls-continue-20170101-story.html |title=Latest 911 calls show chaos in first moments of Pulse shooting |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=November 18, 2016 |accessdate=November 19, 2016 |first=David |last=Harris |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119033033/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-911-calls-continue-20170101-story.html |archivedate=November 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/pulse-911-transcripts-show-moments-after-gunman-opened-fire |title=Pulse 911 transcripts document moments after gunman opened fire |work=WKMG Orlando |date=November 18, 2016 |accessdate=November 19, 2016 |first1=Melodi |last1=Smith |first2=Adrienne |last2=Cutway |first3=Emilee |last3=Speck |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119042127/http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/pulse-911-transcripts-show-moments-after-gunman-opened-fire |archivedate=November 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/11/18/us/pulse-nightclub-911-calls/ |title=Pulse 911 calls: 'They are dying, we're dying' |work=CNN |date=November 18, 2016 |accessdate=November 19, 2016 |first=Steve |last=Almasy |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119015026/http://www.cnn.com/2016/11/18/us/pulse-nightclub-911-calls/ |archivedate=November 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Future of Pulse===\n[[File:Pulse Nightclub, March 2017.jpg|thumb|The Pulse building with the memorial fence in March 2017]]\nOn {{nowrap|September 14}}, 2016, the City of Orlando announced it would pay $4,518 to erect a new fence around the Pulse nightclub on {{nowrap|September 19}}. The fence will feature a commemorative screen-wrap with local artwork that would serve as a memorial to the victims and survivors of the shooting.<ref name=\"WKMG.Changes\">{{cite web |url=http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/new-changes-coming-to-pulse-nightclub |title=New changes coming to Pulse nightclub after shooting |work=WKMG Orlando |date=September 14, 2016 |accessdate=September 14, 2016 |first=Nadeen |last=Yanes |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914164755/http://www.clickorlando.com/news/pulse-orlando-shooting/new-changes-coming-to-pulse-nightclub |archivedate=September 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-nightclub-fence-20160913-story.html |title=City of Orlando to install new fence around Pulse |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=September 14, 2016 |accessdate=September 14, 2016 |first=David |last=Harris |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914071323/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-nightclub-fence-20160913-story.html |archivedate=September 14, 2016}}</ref> It will also be smaller than the nightclub's previous fence, in order to allow for more efficient navigation by passers-by.<ref name=\"WKMG.Changes\"/>\n\nOn {{nowrap|November 8}} the City of Orlando announced its plans to purchase the Pulse nightclub later that month for $2.25 million and turn the site into a memorial for the victims and survivors of the shooting. The announcement was met with praise from Orlando's LGBT community.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.yahoo.com/gma/orlandos-lgbt-community-expresses-relief-city-wants-buy-165927754--abc-news-topstories.html |title=Orlando's LGBT Community Expresses Relief City Wants to Buy Pulse Nightclub |work=Yahoo! GMA |date=November 8, 2016 |accessdate=November 8, 2016 |first=Michael Edison |last=Hayden |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171012203144/https://www.yahoo.com/gma/orlandos-lgbt-community-expresses-relief-city-wants-buy-165927754--abc-news-topstories.html |archivedate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> However, the vote was postponed on {{nowrap|November 15}}, with the city explaining that \"more time was needed to plan a future memorial\", and that there was some discomfort from city officials over having to pay such an amount of money. The vote was expected to be held on or before {{nowrap|December 5}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wftv.com/news/pulse-shooting/orlando-city-leaders-balk-at-pulse-nightclubs-225-million-price-tag/467018471 |title=Vote postponed in $2.25 million Pulse nightclub purchase |work=WFTV Orlando |date=November 15, 2016 |accessdate=November 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116153558/http://www.wftv.com/news/pulse-shooting/orlando-city-leaders-balk-at-pulse-nightclubs-225-million-price-tag/467018471 |archivedate=November 16, 2016}}</ref> In December 2016, the owner declined to sell the nightclub to the city due to emotional attachment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/politics/political-pulse/os-pulse-nightclub-no-sale-orlando-20161205-story.html |title=Pulse nightclub owner says she won't sell to city |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=December 5, 2016 |accessdate=January 16, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116045211/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/politics/political-pulse/os-pulse-nightclub-no-sale-orlando-20161205-story.html |archivedate=January 16, 2017}}</ref> The owner then created the onePULSE Foundation, and in May 2017, announced plans for a [[Pulse Memorial and Museum|memorial site and museum]] slated to open in 2022.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/news/archive/2017/05/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-memorial-museum/525663/ |title=Pulse Nightclub to Become a Memorial and Museum |last=Bendix |first=Aria |work=The Atlantic|access-date=June 12, 2017 |language=en-US |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170623111103/https://www.theatlantic.com/news/archive/2017/05/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-memorial-museum/525663/ |archivedate=June 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/pulse-nightclub-memorial-design_n_5dbb33e8e4b0bb1ea377216d|title=Orlando Unveils Designs For Pulse Memorial, Museum Honoring The 49 Victims|date=2019-10-31|website=HuffPost|language=en|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref>\n\n==Investigations==\n===Classification===\n[[File:Obama receives an update on Orlando shooting.jpg|thumb|President [[Barack Obama]] receives an update in the Oval Office from FBI Director [[James Comey]] and Homeland Security Advisor [[Lisa Monaco]] on the mass shooting.|alt=see caption]]\nOfficials have characterized the shooting as an act of terrorism and a [[hate crime]]. [[FBI Special Agent|FBI Assistant Special Agent in Charge]] Ron Hopper<ref>{{cite press release |last=Hopper |first=Ron |date=June 15, 2016 |title=FBI ASAC Ron Hopper's Remarks at Press Briefing on Pulse Nightclub Shooting Investigation |url=https://www.fbi.gov/tampa/press-releases/2016/fbi-asac-ron-hoppers-remarks-at-press-briefing-on-pulse-nightclub-shooting-investigation |publisher=FBI Tampa |agency=Tampa Press Office |access-date=July 4, 2016 |quote=Good afternoon. My name is Ron Hopper, and I am the Assistant Special Agent in Charge of the FBI's Tampa Field Office overseeing the city of Orlando.}}</ref> called the shooting a hate crime and an act of terrorism;<ref name=\"hatecrime\">{{cite news |last1=McBride |first1=Brian |last2=Hayden |first2=Michael Edison |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Orlando Gay Nightclub Massacre a Hate Crime and Act of Terror, FBI Says |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/investigators-turn-focus-omar-mateens-wife-criminal-charges/story?id=39867320 |publisher=ABC News |access-date=June 17, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616184804/http://abcnews.go.com/US/investigators-turn-focus-omar-mateens-wife-criminal-charges/story?id=39867320 |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref> and Jerry Demings, a sheriff from the Orange County Sheriff's Office, classified it as [[Domestic terrorism in the United States|domestic terrorism]].<ref name=\"abc39789552\" /> City of Orlando Chief of Police John W. Mina said Mateen seemed organized and well-prepared.<ref name=\"AchenbachHolley\">{{cite news |last1=Achenbach |first1=Joel |last2=Holley |first2=Peter |date=June 12, 2016 |title='It was just complete chaos': Orlando massacre survivors on the desperate struggle to stay alive |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-nation/wp/2016/06/12/it-was-just-complete-chaos-survivors-of-orlando-massacre-recall-desperate-struggle-to-stay-alive/ |work=[[The Washington Post]] |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612183118/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-nation/wp/2016/06/12/it-was-just-complete-chaos-survivors-of-orlando-massacre-recall-desperate-struggle-to-stay-alive/ |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> On March 13, 2018, the time of [[#Wife's trial for aiding and obstruction|Mateen's wife's trial]] for aiding the attack, the FBI had still declined to classify it as a hate crime, and the prosecution said it had never contemplated arguing Mateen had targeted gays.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.advocate.com/crime/2018/6/11/why-does-fbi-refuse-call-pulse-massacre-hate-crime|title=Why Does the FBI Refuse to Call the Pulse Massacre a Hate Crime?|date=2018-06-11|website=www.advocate.com|language=en|access-date=2019-10-23}}</ref> It instead only (unsuccessfully) argued she provided material support to a foreign terrorist organization.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.advocate.com/crime/2018/3/13/prosecutors-wont-argue-gay-people-targeted-pulse-shooter-omar-mateen|title=Prosecutors Won't Argue Gay People Targeted by Pulse Shooter Omar Mateen|date=March 13, 2018|website=www.advocate.com}}</ref>\n\nOn {{nowrap|June 13}}, [[FBI Director]] [[James Comey]] told reporters, \"So far, we see no indication that this was a plot directed from outside the United States and we see no indication that he was part of any kind of [[Terrorist cell|network]]\". He said the [[United States Intelligence Community]] was \"highly confident that this killer was [[radicalized]] at least in part through the Internet\",<ref name=\"Shabad\" /> and that the investigation had found \"strong indications of radicalization by this killer and of potential inspiration by [[foreign terrorist organizations]]\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Edwards |first1=Julie |last2=Heavey |first2=Susan |last3=Ahmann |first3=Tim |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Orlando shooter may have been inspired by foreign terrorists -FBI |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/florida-shooting-fbi-idUSW1N17O007 |agency=Reuters |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614130636/http://www.reuters.com/article/florida-shooting-fbi-idUSW1N17O007 |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> Several days after the shooting, the FBI announced on its website that it has become \"the lead law enforcement agency responsible for investigating the shooting at Pulse nightclub in Orlando, Florida, on {{nowrap|June 12}}, 2016\".<ref name=\"G-MenAgency\">{{cite web |url=https://www.fbi.gov/resources/victim-assistance/seeking-victim-information/assistance-for-victims-of-the-pulse-nightclub-shooting-in-orlando |title=Assistance for Victims of the Pulse Nightclub Shooting in Orlando |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |publication-date=June 15, 2016<!--Date is not listed in the article itself, but can be found in the \"Seeking Victim Information\" list here: https://www.fbi.gov/resources/victim-assistance--> |website=Federal Bureau of Investigation |access-date=July 23, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816111857/https://www.fbi.gov/resources/victim-assistance/seeking-victim-information/assistance-for-victims-of-the-pulse-nightclub-shooting-in-orlando |archivedate=August 16, 2016}}</ref> The agency took the lead after the shooting was classified as a terrorist attack due to Mateen's pledge of allegiance to ISIL during the event.<ref name=\"FDLEWrapUp\" />\n\nAccording to Senator [[Ron Johnson (Wisconsin politician)|Ron Johnson]], Mateen searched online for references to the shooting during the attack, and made posts on [[Facebook]] expressing his support for [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]], saying \"You kill innocent women and children by doing us airstrikes. Now taste the Islamic state vengeance.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Blinder|first1=Alan |last2=Robles |first2=Frances |last3=P\u00e9rez-Pe\u00f1a |first3=Richard |title=Omar Mateen Posted to Facebook Amid Orlando Attack, Lawmaker Says |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/17/us/orlando-shooting.html |work=New York Times|date=June 16, 2016|accessdate=February 7, 2019 }}</ref>\n\n===Weapons===\nFederal officials said a [[SIG MCX|SIG Sauer MCX]] semi-automatic rifle and a 9mm [[Glock 17]] semi-automatic pistol were recovered from Mateen's body, along with additional [[Cartridge (firearms)|rounds]].<ref name=\"JansenUSAToday\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Gibbons-Neff |first=Thomas |date=June 14, 2016 |title=The gun the Orlando shooter used was a SIG Sauer MCX, not an AR-15. That doesn't change much. |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/checkpoint/wp/2016/06/14/the-gun-the-orlando-shooter-used-was-not-an-ar-15-that-doesnt-change-much/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615120923/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/checkpoint/wp/2016/06/14/the-gun-the-orlando-shooter-used-was-not-an-ar-15-that-doesnt-change-much/ |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"CNNMotivate\">{{cite news |last1=Ellis |first1=Ralph |last2=Fantz |first2=Ashley |last3=McLaughlin |first3=Eliott C. |last4=Hume |first4=Tim |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Orlando shooting: What motivated a killer? |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/13/us/orlando-nightclub-shooting/ |publisher=CNN |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614114608/http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/13/us/orlando-nightclub-shooting/ |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> Mateen had legally purchased the two guns used in the shooting from a shop in [[Port St. Lucie]]: the SIG Sauer MCX rifle on {{nowrap|June 4}} and the Glock 17 pistol on {{nowrap|June 5}}.<ref name=\"911CallSignificance\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Winter |first1=Tom |last2=Connor |first2=Tracy |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Dealer Who Sold Orlando Massacre Guns: 'I Don't Make the Laws' |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/dealer-who-sold-orlando-massacre-guns-i-don-t-make-n591456 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613203421/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/dealer-who-sold-orlando-massacre-guns-i-don-t-make-n591456 |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> He and law enforcement were reported to have fired a total of over 200 rounds.<ref name=\"TeleLawlerAlexander\" /><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--WFTV-Orlando staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Law enforcement source: 202 rounds fired during Pulse nightclub shooting in Orlando |url=http://www.wsoctv.com/news/trending-now/law-enforcement-source-202-rounds-fired-during-pulse-nightclub-shooting-in-orlando/340948566 |publisher=WSOC-TV |date=June 13, 2016 |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614125056/http://www.wsoctv.com/news/trending-now/law-enforcement-source-202-rounds-fired-during-pulse-nightclub-shooting-in-orlando/340948566 |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"TeleMateenDetails\">{{cite news |last1=Rothwell |first1=James |last2=Alexander |first2=Harriet |last3=Sherlock |first3=Ruth |last4=Akkoc |first4=Raziye |last5=Graham |first5=Chris |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Details emerge about Orlando gunman Omar Mateen |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/14/details-emerge-about-orlando-gunman-omar-mateen/ |work=The Telegraph |access-date=July 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716231855/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/14/details-emerge-about-orlando-gunman-omar-mateen/ |archivedate=July 16, 2016}}</ref> From his car, \"hundreds of rounds\" were found along with a [[.38 caliber]] [[Smith & Wesson]] [[revolver]]; this gun was not used in the shooting.<ref name=\"FDLEWrapUp\" /><ref name=\"CNNMotivate\" />\n\n===Previous FBI investigation of Mateen and cooperation with Seddique===\nMateen became a [[person of interest]] to the FBI in May 2013 and July 2014. The 2013 investigation was opened after he made comments to coworkers about being a member of [[Hezbollah]] and having family connections in [[al-Qaeda]],<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=President Barack Obama and FBI say no clear evidence extremists directed Orlando killer |url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/president-barack-obama-and-fbi-say-no-clear-evidence-extremists-directed-orlando-killer-20160613-gpi99l.html |work=The Sydney Morning Herald |date=June 13, 2016 |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615055529/http://www.smh.com.au/world/president-barack-obama-and-fbi-say-no-clear-evidence-extremists-directed-orlando-killer-20160613-gpi99l.html |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> and that he had ties to [[Nidal Hasan]]\u2014perpetrator of the [[2009 Fort Hood shooting]]\u2014and [[Dzhokhar Tsarnaev|Dzhokhar]] and [[Tamerlan Tsarnaev]]\u2014perpetrators of the [[Boston Marathon bombing]]. According to new documents released on {{nowrap|July 18}}, Mateen said that he made these comments in response to \"a lot of harassment\" and frequent derogatory epithets made by St. Lucie County Sheriff's deputies and his G4S coworkers, who taunted and made jokes about him being a possible Muslim extremist.<ref name=\"New2013MateenTaunts\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Docs: Pulse gunman Omar Mateen taunted at job for being Muslim |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/docs-pulse-gunman-omar-mateen-taunted-at-job-for-being-muslim/ |work=CBS News |date=July 18, 2016 |access-date=July 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719134521/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/docs-pulse-gunman-omar-mateen-taunted-at-job-for-being-muslim/ |archivedate=July 19, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"YahooNoGoPostal\">{{cite news |last=Walsh |first=Michael |date=July 19, 2016 |title=FBI did not think Orlando shooter Omar Mateen would 'go postal' in 2013 |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/fbi-did-not-think-orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-would-go-postal-in-2013-170929145.html |work=Yahoo! News |access-date=July 20, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160721061543/https://www.yahoo.com/news/fbi-did-not-think-orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-would-go-postal-in-2013-170929145.html |archivedate=July 21, 2016}}</ref> The comments resulted in his employer G4S removing Mateen from his post and the county sheriff reporting him to the FBI.<ref name=\"YahooNoGoPostal\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Barry |first1=Dan |last2=Kovaleski |first2=Serge F. |last3=Blinder |first3=Alan |date=June 18, 2016 |title='Always Agitated. Always Mad': Omar Mateen, According to Those Who Knew Him |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/19/us/omar-mateen-gunman-orlando-shooting.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 19, 2016 |quote=In 2013, G4S removed Mr. Mateen from his security post at the St. Lucie County Courthouse after he had made \"inflammatory comments\" about being involved somehow in terrorism. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619033803/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/19/us/omar-mateen-gunman-orlando-shooting.html |archivedate=June 19, 2016}}</ref> The documents also show him saying that he was \"1000% American\" and writing that he was against any \"anti American\" and \"anti humanity\" terrorist organizations.<ref name=\"New2013MateenTaunts\" />\n\nThe 2014 investigation was opened after he was linked to [[Moner Mohammad Abu Salha]],<ref name=\"NYTimes.Early\" /> an [[Jihadist extremism in the United States|American radical]] who committed a [[suicide bombing]] in Syria. Mateen was interviewed three times in connection with the two investigations. Both cases were closed after finding nothing that warranted further investigation.<ref name=\"ABCWhatWeKknow\">{{cite news |last1=Katersky |first1=Aaron |last2=Meek |first2=James Gordon |last3=Margolin |first3=Josh |last4=Hayden |first4=Michael Edison |date=June 12, 2016 |title=What We Know About Omar Mateen, Suspected Orlando Nightclub Shooter |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/omar-mateen-suspected-orlando-night-club-shooter/story?id=39790797 |publisher=ABC News |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612154025/http://abcnews.go.com/US/omar-mateen-suspected-orlando-night-club-shooter/story?id=39790797 |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Shabad\">{{cite news |last=Shabad |first=Rebecca |date=June 13, 2016 |title=FBI Director Comey: \"highly confident\" Orlando shooter radicalized through internet |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/fbi-director-comey-highly-confident-orlando-shooter-radicalized-through-internet/ |publisher=CBS News |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614075936/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/fbi-director-comey-highly-confident-orlando-shooter-radicalized-through-internet/ |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Mass shooting at Pulse nightclub in Orlando, Florida |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/mass-shooting-at-pulse-nightclub-in-orlando-florida/news-story/134cfffa37beca5af509d96d840a5317 |work=The Australian |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |quote=The FBI has described the shooting as \"an act of terrorism\" and say they suspect the shooter had ties to radical Islam. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615084241/http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/mass-shooting-at-pulse-nightclub-in-orlando-florida/news-story/134cfffa37beca5af509d96d840a5317 |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> After the shooting, Director Comey said the FBI will review its work and methods used in the two investigations. When asked if anything could have or should have been done differently in regard to Mateen, or the FBI's intelligence and actions in relation to him, Comey replied, \"So far, the honest answer is, 'I don't think so'\".<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Dearen |first=Jason |last2=Harris |first2=Terrance |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Orlando mourns his dead; gunman may have been 'homegrown' |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/us/articles/2016-06-13/bodies-removed-after-worst-mass-shooting-in-us-history |magazine=U.S. News & World Report |agency=Associated Press |access-date=July 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614115754/http://www.usnews.com/news/us/articles/2016-06-13/bodies-removed-after-worst-mass-shooting-in-us-history |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\nA little over a month after the shooting, the FBI provided more details about its May 2013\u2013March 2014 investigation into Mateen, which was closed after a veteran FBI agent assigned to the case and his supervisor concluded that \"there was just nothing there\" and removed his name from the Terrorist Watchlist. Mateen was interviewed twice during the investigation, and had provided a written statement in which he confessed that he had previously lied to FBI investigators. During the investigation, the FBI had tracked his daily routine using unmarked vehicles, closely examined his phone records, and used two informants to secretly record his face-to-face conversations. The FBI Director said that they could have taken more initiative in gaining access to his social media accounts in 2013, but noted that back then such checks were not yet \"part of [their] investigative DNA\". However, it would not have mattered, as the analysis of Mateen's computer after the shooting showed that his social media accounts, including Facebook, had no ties to any terrorist groups, and that he did not post any \"radical statements\" until the early morning of the shooting. The FBI in 2013 also did not have the [[probable cause]] needed to obtain a search warrant in order to secretly listen to his phone calls or probe into Mateen's computer.<ref name=\"PastFBI2013\">{{cite news |last=Wilber |first=Del Quentin |date=July 14, 2016 |title=The FBI investigated the Orlando mass shooter for 10 months \u2014 and found nothing. Here's why |url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-fbi-investigation-mateen-20160712-snap-story.html |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |access-date=July 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160714112902/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-fbi-investigation-mateen-20160712-snap-story.html |archivedate=July 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn {{nowrap|July 26}}, a Senate homeland security committee chairman sent a four-page letter to the inspector general of the [[U.S. Department of Justice]] (DOJ) requesting an independent review of the FBI's 2013 and 2014 investigations. He wrote that if Mateen had stayed on the FBI watch-list, the federal agency would have been notified if he tried to purchase firearms, in which case \"law enforcement potentially could have uncovered information on social media or elsewhere of Mateen's radicalization\".<ref name=\"GetFBIReviewed\">{{cite news |last=Cherney |first=Elyssa |date=July 27, 2016 |title=Senator: FBI investigations into Pulse gunman need review |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/investigation/os-inspector-general-pulse-mateen-20160727-story.html |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 31, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160731201641/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/investigation/os-inspector-general-pulse-mateen-20160727-story.html |archivedate=July 31, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn March 24, 2018, Sara Sweeney, the assistant attorney prosecuting Mateen's wife, Noor Salman, disclosed to her defense after the discovery period that her father-in-law, Seddique Mateen, was an FBI informant at various points between January 2005 and June 2016.<ref name=\"informant\">{{cite news |date=March 26, 2018 |title=Pulse gunman's father was an FBI informant under criminal investigation, attorneys say |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/03/26/us/noor-salman-pulse-trial-fbi-informant/index.html |work=CNN |accessdate=March 26, 2018}}</ref> Agent Juvenal Martin, who handled the elder Mateen since 2006, said he considered making Omar an informant as well, after investigating and clearing him in 2013.<ref name=Mistrial>{{Cite web|url=https://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-noor-salman-pulse-trial-day-16-story.html|title=Noor Salman trial: Pulse gunman's father revealed as FBI informant, but judge won't dismiss case|first=Krista Torralva, Gal Tziperman|last=Lotan|website=orlandosentinel.com}}</ref><ref name=Greenwald/>\n\n===Searches and possible accomplices===\nUnited States officials said [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]] (ISIL) may have inspired Mateen without training, instructing, or having a direct connection with him.<ref name=\"Stoffel\">{{cite news |last=Stoffel |first=Derek |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Orlando shooting: ISIS quick to claim responsibility but it's likely bluffing, says analyst |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/orlando-shooting-isis-claim-1.3632496 |publisher=[[CBC News]] |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614120153/http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/orlando-shooting-isis-claim-1.3632496 |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Callimach |first=Rukmini |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Was Orlando Shooter Really Acting for ISIS? For ISIS, It's All the Same |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/orlando-omar-mateen-isis.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613021601/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/13/us/orlando-omar-mateen-isis.html |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Abdelaty |first1=Ali |last2=Aboulenein |first2=Ahmed |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Islamic State claims responsibility for Orlando nightclub shooting |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-claim-idUSKCN0YY0VU |agency=Reuters |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612220123/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-claim-idUSKCN0YY0VU |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> Investigators have said no evidence linking Mateen to the group has emerged, and have cautioned that the shooting may have been ISIL-inspired without being ISIL-directed,<ref name=\"guardian20160612\">{{cite news |last=Burke |first=Jason |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Was Pulse nightclub shooter Omar Mateen directed by Isis? |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/12/orlando-nightclub-shooter-omar-mateen-isis-affiliation |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613082854/http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/12/orlando-nightclub-shooter-omar-mateen-isis-affiliation |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> as was the case in the [[2015 San Bernardino attack|{{nowrap|December 2}}, 2015 attack]] in [[San Bernardino, California]].<ref name=\"AlvarezAnguish\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Weaver |first1=Jay |last2=Ovalle |first2=David |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Terror enemy No. 1: Lone wolves like Orlando killer Omar Mateen |url=http://www.bradenton.com/news/state/florida/article83866832.html |work=The Miami Herald |access-date=June 15, 2016 |quote=One person, perhaps beset by some mix of mental and personal issues, who 'self-radicalizes,' proclaiming an affinity for Islamic extremists and acting on it alone with easily accessible high-powered weapons. That's what investigators believe the 29-year-old security guard from Fort Pierce did on Sunday morning, killing 49 and wounding 53 others at the Pulse nightclub in Orlando. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616192833/http://www.bradenton.com/news/state/florida/article83866832.html |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref> [[Yoram Schweitzer]] of the Israeli [[Institute for National Security Studies (Israel)|Institute for National Security Studies]] posited that Mateen associated the attack with ISIL to add notoriety, and said it was very unlikely that ISIL had known of him before the shooting.<ref name=\"Stoffel\" />\n\nOn {{nowrap|June 16}}, [[Director of the Central Intelligence Agency]] [[John O. Brennan|John Brennan]] told the Senate Intelligence Committee that his agency was \"unable to uncover any link\" between Mateen and ISIL.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ackerman |first=Spencer |date=June 16, 2016 |title=CIA has not found any link between Orlando killer and Isis, says agency chief |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/16/cia-orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-isis-pulse-nightclub-attack |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=June 17, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616204927/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/16/cia-orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-isis-pulse-nightclub-attack |archivedate=June 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the shooting, officers from multiple federal, state, and local law-enforcement agencies (including the FBI, [[Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives]], [[Florida Department of Law Enforcement]] (FDLE), [[St. Lucie County]] Sheriff's Office, and Fort Pierce Police Department) converged on Mateen's home in [[Fort Pierce]] and another home in [[Port St. Lucie]]. A bomb squad checked Mateen's Fort Pierce home for explosives.<ref>{{cite news |last=Jones |first=Elliott |date=June 12, 2016 |title=PSL mayor: 'We have heavy hearts but steely resolve' |url=http://www.tcpalm.com/news/crime/st-lucie-county/local-federal-law-enforcement-officials-at-fort-pierce-home-in-connection-with-orlando-killings-3515-382609381.html |work=[[Treasure Coast Newspapers]] |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612163617/http://www.tcpalm.com/news/crime/st-lucie-county/local-federal-law-enforcement-officials-at-fort-pierce-home-in-connection-with-orlando-killings-3515-382609381.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> In June 2016, the [[House Intelligence Committee]] said that United States investigators \"are searching for details about the [[Saudi Arabia]] trips Mateen made in 2011 and 2012.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Paletta |first1=Damian |last2=Shallwani |first2=Pervaiz |date=June 16, 2016 |title=Orlando Shooter Traveled to Saudi Arabia on Trip Organized By NYU Center |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-shooter-traveled-to-saudi-arabia-on-trip-organized-by-nyu-center-1466122172 |work=Wall Street Journal |access-date=June 21, 2016 |url-access=subscription  |quote=Rep. Adam Schiff, the top Democrat on the House Intelligence Committee, said law-enforcement officials are searching for details about the Saudi Arabia trips Mateen made in 2011 and 2012 for a number of reasons. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160620191901/http://www.wsj.com/articles/orlando-shooter-traveled-to-saudi-arabia-on-trip-organized-by-nyu-center-1466122172 |archivedate=June 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Perez |first1=Evan |last2=Brown |first2=Pamela |last3=Almasy |first3=Steve |date=June 18, 2016 |title=Orlando shooting: Killer's behavior had long been an issue |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/06/17/us/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen/ |work=CNN |access-date=June 21, 2016 |quote=New York University confirmed the killer traveled on a pilgrimage to holy sites in Saudi Arabia organized by the university's Islamic Center in 2012. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160621034655/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/06/17/us/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen |archivedate=June 21, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Barry |first1=Dan |last2=Kovaleski |first2=Serge F. |last3=Blinder |first3=Alan |last4=Mashal |first4=Mujib |date=June 18, 2016 |title='Always Agitated. Always Mad': Omar Mateen, According to Those Who Knew Him |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/19/us/omar-mateen-gunman-orlando-shooting.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 21, 2016 |quote=He was religious \u2014 he made at least two Islamic pilgrimages to Saudi Arabia \u2014 but he never expressed sympathy for radical Islamists or terrorists, she [Mateen's ex-wife] said. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160620232947/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/19/us/omar-mateen-gunman-orlando-shooting.html |archivedate=June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Senate Intelligence Committee]] member [[Angus King]] said that Mateen's second wife appears to have had \"some knowledge of what was going on\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Smith |first=David |date=June 15, 2016 |title=FBI checking if Orlando shooter's wife knew attack plan but didn't warn police |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/14/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-omar-mateen-wife |newspaper=The Guardian |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615001910/http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/jun/14/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-omar-mateen-wife |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Perez |first1=Evan |last2=Brown |first2=Pamela |date=June 14, 2016 |title=Source: Orlando gunman told wife of interest in a terror attack |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/14/us/orlando-gunman-omar-mateen-wife-fbi/ |publisher=CNN |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160622185329/http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/14/us/orlando-gunman-omar-mateen-wife-fbi/ |archivedate=June 22, 2016}}</ref> Media reports, citing anonymous law enforcement officials, said she was with Mateen as he scouted possible [[Orlando metropolitan area|Orlando-area]] targets (including the Walt Disney World Resort's [[Disney Springs]] and the Pulse nightclub) and that she was also with him when he purchased ammunition and a holster in the months leading up to the attack.<ref>{{cite news |first=Evan |last=Perez |first2=Shimon |last2=Prokupecz |first3=Holly |last3=Yan |title=Omar Mateen scouted Disney complex, Pulse, official says |date=June 15, 2016 |accessdate=July 8, 2016 |website=CNN |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/14/us/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160703125503/http://www.cnn.com/2016/06/14/us/orlando-shooter-omar-mateen |archivedate=July 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Stein |first1=Letitia |last2=Edwards |first2=Julia |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Orlando shooting probe focuses on gunman's wife |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-idUSKCN0Z017C |agency=Reuters |access-date=June 15, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614224303/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-idUSKCN0Z017C |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Williams |first1=Pete |last2=Winter |first2=Tom |last3=Dienst |first3=Jonathan |last4=Dilanian |first4=Ken |date=June 15, 2016 |title=Omar Mateen's Wife Tried to Talk Him Out of Orlando Attack, Sources Say |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/omar-mateen-s-wife-tried-talk-him-out-orlando-attack-n592051 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=June 15, 2016 |quote=Omar Mateen's wife, Noor Zahi Salman, told the FBI she was with him when he bought ammunition and a holster, several officials familiar with the case said. She told the FBI that she once drove him to the gay nightclub, Pulse, because he wanted to scope it out. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615010907/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/omar-mateen-s-wife-tried-talk-him-out-orlando-attack-n592051 |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Trial and acquittal of shooter's wife====\nMateen's second wife, Noor Salman, was arrested in January 2017, at her home in [[Rodeo, California]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sfgate.com/news/article/Wife-of-Orlando-nightclub-gunman-arrested-outside-10860380.php |title=Wife of Orlando nightclub gunman arrested outside SF |work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |date=January 16, 2017 |accessdate=January 16, 2017 |first1=Evan |last1=Sernoffsky |first2=Kimberly |last2=Veklerov |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116175434/http://www.sfgate.com/news/article/Wife-of-Orlando-nightclub-gunman-arrested-outside-10860380.php |archivedate=January 16, 2017}}</ref> She was [[criminal charge|charged]] in federal court in Orlando with [[aiding and abetting]] as well as [[obstruction of justice]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/noor-salman-wife-orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-arrested-n707451 |title=Noor Salman, Wife of Orlando Shooter Omar Mateen, Arrested |publisher=NBC News |date=January 16, 2017 |accessdate=January 16, 2017 |first1=Andrew |last1=Blankstein |first2=Tracy |last2=Connor |first3=Ayman |last3=Mohyeldin |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116171321/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/noor-salman-wife-orlando-shooter-omar-mateen-arrested-n707451 |archivedate=January 16, 2017}}</ref> Federal prosecutors accused her of knowing that Mateen was planning an attack.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/orlando-gunman-s-wife-noor-salman-accused-misleading-police-n707731 |title=Orlando Gunman's Wife Noor Salman Knew His Plan, Feds Say |work=NBC News |date=January 17, 2017 |accessdate=January 17, 2017 |first1=Joe |last1=Fryer |first2=Tracy |last2=Connor |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117150157/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/orlando-gunman-s-wife-noor-salman-accused-misleading-police-n707731 |archivedate=January 17, 2017}}</ref> Salman pleaded not guilty to the charges.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/orlando-massacre-gunman-s-wife-noor-salman-pleads-not-guilty-n708461 |title=Orlando Massacre Gunman's Wife, Noor Salman, Pleads Not Guilty |work=NBC News |date=January 18, 2017 |accessdate=January 18, 2017 |first1=Joe |last1=Fryer |first2=Tracy |last2=Connor |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118191914/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/orlando-massacre-gunman-s-wife-noor-salman-pleads-not-guilty-n708461 |archivedate=January 18, 2017}}</ref> Salman moved to dismiss the obstruction charge; this motion was denied by U.S. District Judge [[Paul G. Byron]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-nightclub-shooting-noor-salman-judge-wont-dismiss-count-against-omar-mateens-wife/ |title=Orlando nightclub shooting: Judge won't dismiss charge against gunman's wife|access-date=July 19, 2017 |language=en |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170720054126/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-nightclub-shooting-noor-salman-judge-wont-dismiss-count-against-omar-mateens-wife/ |archivedate=July 20, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"GoldmanWife\">{{cite news |last1=Goldman |first1=Adam |title=Orlando Gunman's Wife Breaks Silence: 'I Was Unaware' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/02/us/politics/orlando-shooting-omar-mateen-noor-salman.html?_r=1 |accessdate=January 29, 2017 |newspaper=New York Times |date=November 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\nSalman's trial took place in March 2018.<ref name=\"Roulette\">Joey Roulette, [https://www.reuters.com/article/us-orlando-shooting/federal-prosecutors-to-make-final-case-against-orlando-gunmans-widow-idUSKBN1H41CF Jury in trial of Orlando gunman's widow starts deliberations], Reuters (March 28, 2018).</ref> During the trial, the prosecution revealed it withheld information during discovery that Salman's confession of helping scout potential attack locations was not true based on cell phone evidence, and that the FBI knew this even though it had been used to deny her [[bail]].<ref name=Greenwald>{{cite web |url=https://theintercept.com/2018/03/22/at-trial-of-omar-mateens-wife-judges-questioning-reveals-a-huge-hole-in-prosecutions-case-and-deceit-by-prosecutors/ |title=At Trial of Omar Mateen's Wife, Judge's Questioning Reveals a Huge Hole in Prosecution's Case and Deceit by Prosecutors |first=Glenn |last=Greenwald |first2=Murtaza |last2=Hussain |date=March 22, 2018 |website=The Intercept}}</ref> The defense also sought to dismiss the charges or declare a mistrial on [[Brady disclosure|''Brady'' disclosure]] grounds after this disclosure, and after the prosecution disclosed during the trial that Seddique Mateen had been a confidential FBI informant \"at various points in time between January 2005 through June 2016.\"<ref>Eric Levenson & Tina Burnside, [https://www.cnn.com/2018/03/26/us/noor-salman-pulse-trial-fbi-informant/index.html Judge denies motion to drop case against widow of Pulse gunman], CNN (March 26, 2018).</ref> The court denied Salman's motion to dismiss the charges or declare a mistrial.<ref name=Mistrial/><ref name=\"Roulette\"/> On March 30 the jury acquitted Salman of both charges.<ref>Patricia Mazzei, [https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/30/us/noor-salman-pulse-trial-verdict.html \"Noor Salman Acquitted in Pulse Nightclub Shooting], ''New York Times'' (March 30, 2018).</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/c5613430d459423a9e45b1885bad29f3|title=Widow of Orlando nightclub gunman is acquitted in the attack|last=Lush|first=Tamara|date=March 30, 2018|website=AP NEWS|access-date=February 21, 2019}}</ref> One survivor of the shooting called the acquittal \"devastating\" for the victims of the shooting.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/transcript/pulse-survivor-acquittal-of-shooters-wife-is-devastating|title=Pulse survivor: Acquittal of shooter's wife is 'devastating'|date=March 31, 2018|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=February 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Progress===\nIn July 2016, law enforcement officials reported that the FBI\u2014after conducting \"interviews and an examination of his computer and other electronic media\"\u2014has not found any evidence that Mateen targeted Pulse because the nightclub was a venue for gays or whether the attack was motivated by homophobia. According to witnesses, he did not make any homophobic comments during the shooting. Also, nothing has been found that confirms the speculation that he was gay and used gay dating apps; however, the FBI \"has found evidence that Mateen was cheating on his wife with other women\". Officials noted that \"there is nothing to suggest that he attempted to cover up his tracks by deleting files\". Generally, \"a complete picture of what motivated Mateen remains murky and may never be known since he was killed in a shootout with police and did not leave a manifesto\".<ref name=\"FBINoEvidence\">{{cite news |last=Goldman |first=Adam |date=July 15, 2016 |title=FBI has found no evidence that Orlando shooter targeted Pulse because it was a gay club |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/no-evidence-so-far-to-suggest-orlando-shooter-targeted-club-because-it-was-gay/2016/07/14/a7528674-4907-11e6-acbc-4d4870a079da_story.html |work=The Washington Post |access-date=July 16, 2016 |quote=The FBI, however, has been unable to verify that Mateen used gay dating apps and instead has found evidence that Mateen was cheating on his wife with other women. Officials said there is nothing to suggest that he attempted to cover up his tracks by deleting files. They also added he did not make gay slurs during the shooting spree inside the club, based on witnesses. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113050506/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/no-evidence-so-far-to-suggest-orlando-shooter-targeted-club-because-it-was-gay/2016/07/14/a7528674-4907-11e6-acbc-4d4870a079da_story.html |archivedate=November 13, 2016}}</ref> The FBI has yet to conclude its investigation.<ref name=\"FDLEWrapUp\" /><ref name=\"FDLE.FBIStatus\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=FDLE turns Pulse probe over to prosecutor |url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/sns-bc-fl--nightclub-shooting-florida-20160824-story.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160915124042/http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/sns-bc-fl--nightclub-shooting-florida-20160824-story.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=September 15, 2016 |newspaper=Sun Sentinel |agency=Associated Press |date=August 24, 2016 |access-date=August 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2016, an imam for a mosque in [[Kissimmee, Florida|Kissimmee]] released video footage showing what appeared to be Mateen on {{nowrap|June 8}}, four days before the shooting, praying for about ten minutes. The imam said Mateen was praying there with his wife and child, and had no verbal exchanges with any of the other attendants. Though the FBI was already in possession of the mosque's security recordings, the video footage was released to the public only after [[2016 New York and New Jersey bombings|a series of bombings or bombing attempts in New York and New Jersey]], and [[St. Cloud, Minnesota mall stabbing|a mass stabbing at a Minnesota shopping mall]] in September 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/features/religion/religion-world/os-kissimmee-islamic-center-mateen-video-the-american-muslim-leadership-council-20160928-story.html |title=Imam: Omar Mateen prayed at Kissimmee mosque days before attack |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=September 28, 2016 |accessdate=September 29, 2016 |first=Bethany |last=Rodgers |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160930032311/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/features/religion/religion-world/os-kissimmee-islamic-center-mateen-video-the-american-muslim-leadership-council-20160928-story.html |archivedate=September 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Evaluations of performance of law enforcement===\nAt the request of John Mina, the Orlando chief of police, the [[U.S. Department of Justice]]'s [[Office of Community Oriented Policing Services]] (COPS) conducted a third-party \"after-action assessment\" of the Orlando Police Department's response to the shooting and its overall preparedness.<ref>{{cite news |last=Harris |first=David |date=July 9, 2016 |title=Chief Mina asks for DOJ's help to find group to conduct review into Pulse shooting |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-mina-interview-20160708-story.html |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 11, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160710152354/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-mina-interview-20160708-story.html |archivedate=July 10, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Helsel |first=Phil |date=July 17, 2016 |title=Justice Department to Review Police Response to Pulse Nightclub Shooting |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/justice-department-review-police-response-pulse-nightclub-shooting-n611031 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=July 17, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160717055452/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/orlando-nightclub-massacre/justice-department-review-police-response-pulse-nightclub-shooting-n611031 |archivedate=July 17, 2016}}</ref> COPS commissioned the [[Police Foundation]] to prepare the report, which was released in December 2017. The report concluded that the Orlando Police Department response \"was appropriate and consistent with national guidelines and best practices\" and saved lives.<ref name=Lotan>Gal Tziperman Lotan, [http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-shooting-after-action-report-20170707-story.html Federal report on Pulse: Authorities performed well but more training needed], ''Orlando Sentinel'' (December 18, 2017).</ref> The report stated: \"The initial tactical response was consistent with the OPD's active shooter training and recognized promising practices. However, as the incident became more complex and prolonged, transitioning from a barricaded suspect with hostages to an act of terrorism, the OPD's operational tactics and strategies were challenged by the increasing threat posed by the suspect's claim of improvised explosive devices inside the club and in vehicles surrounding the club.\"<ref name=Lotan/> The report authors noted that they lacked access to FBI reports and other data about the crime scene and shooter, and did not have information about \"potential law enforcement friendly fire.\"<ref name=Lotan/>\n\nIn April 2017, the ''[[Orlando Sentinel]]'' obtained a copy of a 78-page presentation given by Mina to some ten police groups located around the world, which discussed the OPD's response to the attack and what it has learned. The presentation offered a comprehensive timeline of the attack and included diagrams and still photos from [[body camera]] footage showing officers in their initial confrontation with Mateen. According to the presentation, 500 interviews were conducted, 1,600 leads were followed up on, more than 950 pieces of evidence were collected, and more than 300 people were subpoenaed.<ref name=orlandosentinel1/>\n\nIn December 2016, the [[Florida Department of Law Enforcement]] completed a 35-page \"after-action report\" about its response to the nightclub during the shooting.<ref name=\"HarrisAfterAction\">Alex Harris, [http://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/article169442562.html FDLE agents did the best they could at Pulse, report concludes], ''Miami Herald'' (August 25, 2017).</ref><ref name=\"AfterActionSentinel\">{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-orlando-fdle-after-action-report-20170809-story.html |title=Pulse nightclub shooting: FDLE releases review of agency's response, recommends changes |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=August 24, 2017 |first=Christal |last=Hayesl}}</ref> The report was publicly released in August 2017 after a public records request made by the ''Orlando Sentinel''.<ref name=\"HarrisAfterAction\"/><ref name=\"AfterActionSentinel\"/> The report generally praised the FDLE's handling of the nightclub shootings, but detailed the agency's difficulties in notifying the dead's families and complications arising from its inter-agency policies, which led to them not immediately sharing information about the shooting with federal investigators.<ref name=\"HarrisAfterAction\"/><ref name=\"AfterActionSentinel\"/>\n\n==Reactions==\n{{Main|Reactions to the Orlando nightclub shooting}}\n[[File:San Francisco vigil for Orlando - 5.jpg|thumb|[[San Francisco City Hall]] lit in LGBT rainbow flag in honor to the victims of the shooting]]\n[[Governor of Florida|Florida governor]] [[Rick Scott]] expressed support for all affected, and said the state emergency operations center was monitoring the incident.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.flgov.com/2016/06/12/gov-scott-we-will-devote-every-resource-available-to-assist-with-orlando-shooting/ |title=Gov. Scott: We Will Devote Every Resource Available to Assist with Orlando Shooting |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |date=June 12, 2016 |website=Governor of Florida |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615140401/http://www.flgov.com/2016/06/12/gov-scott-we-will-devote-every-resource-available-to-assist-with-orlando-shooting/ |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> Scott declared a [[state of emergency]] for [[Orange County, Florida]],<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Video with a short description; no by-line--> |title=Florida Gov Rick Scott declares a state of emergency following Orlando mass shooting |url=https://www.usatoday.com/videos/news/2016/06/12/85791790/ |website=USA Today |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612203139/http://www.usatoday.com/videos/news/2016/06/12/85791790/ |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> and [[Mayor of Orlando|Orlando mayor]] [[Buddy Dyer]] declared a state of emergency for the city.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Orlando nightclub shooting: Mayor declares state of emergency |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-36510761 |agency=BBC News |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612214326/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-36510761 |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Dyer |first=Buddy |date=June 12, 2016 |title=City of Orlando Update 10:20 a.m. |url=http://www.cityoforlando.net/mayor/2016/06/city-of-orlando-update-1020-a-m/ |publisher=[[City of Orlando]] |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615041247/http://www.cityoforlando.net/mayor/2016/06/city-of-orlando-update-1020-a-m/ |archivedate=June 15, 2016}}</ref> On {{nowrap|June 24}}, Scott directed that 49 state flags be flown for 49 days in front of the [[Florida State Capitol|Florida Historic Capitol]] in Tallahassee, with the name, age, and photo of every victim displayed beneath each flag.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Florida flying 49 flags for 49 days for Orlando shooting victims |url=http://www.cbs46.com/story/32302788/florida-flying-49-flags-for-49-days-for-orlando-shooting-victims |work=CNN |publisher=CBS 49 |date=July 1, 2016 |publication-date=June 24, 2016 |access-date=July 14, 2016}}{{Dead link|date=September 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Obama personnel|Obama administration]] expressed its condolences to the victims. President [[Barack Obama]] ordered that \"the federal government provide any assistance necessary to pursue the investigation and support the community.\"<ref name=\"PressSec\">{{cite press release |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Statement by the Press Secretary |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2016/06/12/statement-press-secretary |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=[[White House Office of the Press Secretary]] |date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612230615/https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2016/06/12/statement-press-secretary |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> In a speech, he described the shooting as an \"[[hate crime|act of hate]]\" and an \"[[act of terror]]\".<ref name=\"cbslocal\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Mallin |first=Alexander |date=June 12, 2016 |title=President Obama Calls Orlando Shooting an 'Act of Terror' |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/president-obama-deliver-statement-orlando-shooting/story?id=39794617 |publisher=[[ABC News]] |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613005718/http://abcnews.go.com/US/president-obama-deliver-statement-orlando-shooting/story?id=39794617 |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Obama calls Orlando shooting an 'act of terror, act of hate' |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-whitehouse-idUSKCN0YY0UX |agency=Reuters |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612193100/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-whitehouse-idUSKCN0YY0UX |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> He also issued a proclamation on {{nowrap|June 12}} ordering United States flags upon non-private grounds and buildings around the country and abroad to be lowered to [[half-staff]] until sundown, {{nowrap|June 16}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2016/06/12/presidential-proclamation-honoring-victims-attack-orlando-florida |title=Presidential Proclamation \u2013 Honoring the Victims of the Attack in Orlando, Florida |last=Obama |first=Barack |author-link=Barack Obama |date=June 12, 2016 |publisher=White House Office of the Press Secretary |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613072642/https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2016/06/12/presidential-proclamation-honoring-victims-attack-orlando-florida |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> He and Vice President [[Joe Biden]] traveled to Orlando on {{nowrap|June 16}} to lay flowers at a memorial and visit the victims' families.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Zezima |first1=Katie |last2=Nakashima |first2=Ellen |last3=Berman |first3=Mark |date=June 16, 2016 |title='Our hearts are broken, too': Obama visits survivors of Orlando rampage |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-nation/wp/2016/06/16/obama-looks-toward-grieving-orlando-in-visit-as-political-showdowns-expand-after-massacre/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=June 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617053721/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-nation/wp/2016/06/16/obama-looks-toward-grieving-orlando-in-visit-as-political-showdowns-expand-after-massacre/ |archivedate=June 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\nMany American Muslims, including community leaders, swiftly condemned the shooting.<ref name=\"Gunaratna\">{{cite news |last=Gunaratna |first=Shanika |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Muslim Americans rush to condemn Orlando massacre |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-muslims-condemn-attack/ |publisher=CBS News |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614011325/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/orlando-shooting-pulse-nightclub-muslims-condemn-attack/ |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"CookeAli\">{{cite news |last1=Cooke |first1=Kristina |last2=Ali |first2=Idrees |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Muslim leaders condemn Florida massacre, brace for backlash |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-mosques-idUSKCN0YZ2K6 |agency=Reuters |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614025447/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-florida-shooting-mosques-idUSKCN0YZ2K6 |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> Prayer vigils for the victims were held at mosques across the country.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lozano |first=Carlos |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Several vigils are planned around Southern California for the Orlando shooting victims |url=https://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-vigils-20160612-snap-story.html |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612224556/http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-vigils-20160612-snap-story.html |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Galvez |first=Samantha |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Harrisburg mosque holds prayer vigil for Orlando victims |url=http://abc27.com/2016/06/13/harrisburg-mosque-holds-prayer-vigil-for-orlando-victims/ |publisher=[[WHTM-TV]] |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613234454/http://abc27.com/2016/06/13/harrisburg-mosque-holds-prayer-vigil-for-orlando-victims/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Hutchison |first=Ben |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Milwaukee mosque holds prayer vigil for Orlando shooting victims |url=http://www.wisn.com/news/local-mosque-holds-prayer-vigil-for-orlando-shooting-victims/40026204 |publisher=WISN |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619103641/http://www.wisn.com/news/local-mosque-holds-prayer-vigil-for-orlando-shooting-victims/40026204 |archivedate=June 19, 2016}}</ref> The Florida mosque where Mateen sometimes prayed issued a statement condemning the attack and offering condolences to the victims.<ref>{{cite news |last=Blinder |first=Alan |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Fort Pierce Mosque in Florida Condemns Attack |url=https://www.nytimes.com/live/orlando-nightclub-shooting-live-updates/ft-pierce-mosque/ |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=June 14, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614081856/http://www.nytimes.com/live/orlando-nightclub-shooting-live-updates/ft-pierce-mosque/ |archivedate=June 14, 2016}}</ref> The [[Council on American\u2013Islamic Relations]] called the attack \"monstrous\" and offered its condolences to the victims. CAIR Florida urged Muslims to donate blood even while observing the month of [[Ramadan]] - which requires Muslims to fast from dawn to dusk - and contribute funds in support of the victims' families.<ref name=\"Gunaratna\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Afshar |first1=Paradise |last2=Seiden |first2=Michael |date=June 13, 2016 |title=Muslim community condemns Orlando attack, calls for blood donations |url=http://www.local10.com/news/muslim-community-condemns-orlando-attack-calls-for-blood-donations |publisher=[[WPLG]] |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613112143/http://www.local10.com/news/muslim-community-condemns-orlando-attack-calls-for-blood-donations |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> Some Muslim groups called on members to break their Ramadan fast to be able to donate blood.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/detroit-muslim-group-donates-blood-during-ramadan-for-orlando-shooting-2016-6?IR=T |title=A Detroit Muslim group is setting the bar for how we should respond to the Orlando shooting |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211155647/http://www.businessinsider.com/detroit-muslim-group-donates-blood-during-ramadan-for-orlando-shooting-2016-6?IR=T |archivedate=February 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe [[United Nations Security Council]] issued a statement condemning the shooting for \"targeting persons as a result of their sexual orientation\". It was supported by some countries that suppress homosexual behavior and discussion, such as Egypt and Russia.<ref>{{cite news |last=Sengupta |first=Somini |date=June 14, 2016 |title=After Orlando, Gay Rights Moves off Diplomatic Back Burner |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/15/world/united-nations-gay-rights-diplomacy.html |work=The New York Times |access-date=June 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619084340/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/15/world/united-nations-gay-rights-diplomacy.html |archivedate=June 19, 2016}}</ref> [[Samantha Power]], United States Ambassador to the UN, led a group of 17 UN ambassadors on a visit to the historic LGBT landmark Stonewall Inn to express their support for LGBT rights in response to the shooting.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lederer |first=Judith M. |date=June 16, 2016 |title=17 UN envoys vow to fight for LGBT rights around the world |url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/8f7687d92f124d51adb1bde977888e16/17-un-envoys-vow-fight-lgbt-rights-around-world |agency=Associated Press |access-date=June 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618155341/http://www.bigstory.ap.org/article/8f7687d92f124d51adb1bde977888e16/17-un-envoys-vow-fight-lgbt-rights-around-world |archivedate=June 18, 2016}}</ref> Countries that released their own statements condemning the shooting include Afghanistan, Egypt, Saudi Arabia, [[Qatar]], Iran, the [[United Arab Emirates]], [[Kuwait]] and Turkey.<ref>{{cite news |last=Habib |first=Samar |date=June 17, 2016 |title=Arab regimes' sympathy over the Orlando massacre may seem hypocritical. But it's a start. |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2016/06/17/arab-regimes-sympathy-over-the-orlando-massacre-may-seem-hypocritical-but-its-a-start/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=June 19, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619022525/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2016/06/17/arab-regimes-sympathy-over-the-orlando-massacre-may-seem-hypocritical-but-its-a-start/ |archivedate=June 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\nMany people on [[social media]] and elsewhere, including [[2016 United States presidential election]] candidates, members of [[United States Congress|Congress]], other political figures, foreign leaders, and various celebrities, expressed their shock at the event and extended their condolences to those affected.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kelly |first=Erin |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Trump, Clinton, congressional leaders react to Orlando shooting |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2016/06/12/trump-clinton-orlando-shooting-reaction-congress/85787942/ |work=USA Today |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612161550/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2016/06/12/trump-clinton-orlando-shooting-reaction-congress/85787942/ |archivedate=June 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Politicians, officials across the world react to mass shooting at Orlando nightclub |url=http://www.denverpost.com/2016/06/12/reaction-to-orlando-nightclub-mass-shooting/ |work=The Denver Post |agency=Associated Press |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613110523/http://www.denverpost.com/2016/06/12/reaction-to-orlando-nightclub-mass-shooting/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> Vigils were held around the world to mourn those who were killed in the shooting, including one held at the banks of [[Lake Eola Park]] on {{nowrap|June 19}} that attracted 50,000 people.<ref>{{cite news |last=Neale |first=Rick |date=June 12, 2016 |title=Across USA, Vigils Honor Orlando Victims |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2016/06/12/vigil-for-orlando-shooting/85804836/ |work=USA Today |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613005620/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2016/06/12/vigil-for-orlando-shooting/85804836/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Photos: The World Mourns Orlando Shooting Victims |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/photos-the-world-mourns-orlando-victims-1465775630 |work=The Wall Street Journal |date=June 12, 2016 |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613005920/http://www.wsj.com/articles/photos-the-world-mourns-orlando-victims-1465775630 |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line--> |title=Vigils Around the World Show Solidarity with Orlando |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/vigils-around-the-world-show-solidarity-with-orlando/article30413726/ |work=The Globe and Mail |date=June 13, 2016 |access-date=June 13, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160613145727/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/vigils-around-the-world-show-solidarity-with-orlando/article30413726/ |archivedate=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOnePulse Foundation, a charity organization created by a Pulse owner on {{nowrap|July 7}}, filed documents with a plan to fund and build a memorial at the nightclub. The foundation is collaborating with the city of Orlando to determine the location of the memorial.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ortega |first=Jennifer |date=July 27, 2016 |title=Pulse nightclub to become permanent memorial after mass shooting |url=http://wtvr.com/2016/07/27/pulse-nightclub-to-become-permanent-memorial-after-mass-shooting/ |publisher=WTVR CBS 6 |access-date=July 28, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728143800/http://wtvr.com/2016/07/27/pulse-nightclub-to-become-permanent-memorial-after-mass-shooting/ |archivedate=July 28, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Brinkmann |first=Paul |date=July 26, 2016 |title=Plan for a memorial at Pulse put in writing |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-memorial-coming-together-20160726-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=July 28, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160727144448/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-memorial-coming-together-20160726-story.html |archivedate=July 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Brinkmann |first=Paul |date=August 16, 2016 |title=Hollywood fundraiser will support Orlando shooting victims, memorial |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-fundraiser-hollywood-lineup-20160816-story.html |work=Orlando Sentinel |access-date=August 17, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817130022/http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/pulse-orlando-nightclub-shooting/os-pulse-fundraiser-hollywood-lineup-20160816-story.html |archivedate=August 17, 2016}}</ref> The non-profit organization also plans to start a fundraising campaign to provide financial help to the surviving victims who were injured and the families of the 49 who were killed.<ref>{{cite news |last=Moll-Ramirez |first=Victoria |date=August 1, 2016 |title=Pulse Orlando Night Club Fundraising to Open Memorial for Victims |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/pulse-orlando-night-club-become-memorial-victims-n620831 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=August 1, 2016 |quote='The OnePulseFoundation was established to raise funds for victims of the June 12 tragedy as well as for a memorial,' the statement reads. 'No monies have been collected at this time.' |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160802153924/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/pulse-orlando-night-club-become-memorial-victims-n620831 |archivedate=August 2, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn the aftermath of the 2018 trial, some media re-assessed the reactions, possible motives and media narrative of the shooting.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jane Coaston |title=New evidence shows the Pulse nightclub shooting wasn't about anti-LGBTQ hate |url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2018/4/5/17202026/pulse-shooting-lgbtq-trump-terror-hate |accessdate=April 8, 2018 |work=Vox |date=April 8, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Jeltsen HuffPost\">{{cite web |last=Jeltsen |first=Melissa |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/noor-salman-pulse-massacre-wrong_us_5ac29ebae4b04646b6454dc2 |title=Everyone Got The Pulse Massacre Story Completely Wrong |date=April 5, 2018 |work=HuffPost |accessdate=July 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==See also==\n{{wikinews|At least 50 dead in shooting at Florida nightclub}}\n* [[Gun violence in the United States]]\n* [[Gun law in the United States]]\n* [[Gun politics in the United States]]\n* [[2016 United States House of Representatives sit-in]]\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Chris Murphy gun control filibuster]]\n* [[LGBT in Islam]]\n* [[List of Islamist terrorist attacks]]\n* [[List of rampage killers (religious, political or racial crimes)]]\n* [[List of terrorist incidents in June 2016]]\n* [[Terrorism in the United States]]\n* [[Domestic terrorism in the United States]]\n* [[Violence against LGBT people]]\n* ''[[Our Happy Hours|Our Happy Hours: LGBT Voices from the Gay Bars]]''\n* [[Mass shootings in the United States]]\n{{End div col}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Florida|Hispanic and Latino American|LGBT}}\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|2016 Orlando nightclub shooting}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* Frank Straub, Jack Cambria, Jane Castor, Ben Gorban, Brett Meade, David Waltemeyer, and Jennifer Zeunik, ''[https://www.policefoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Orlando-Pulse.pdf Rescue, Response, and Resilience: A Critical Incident Review of the Orlando Public Safety Response to the Attack on the Pulse Nightclub]'', [[Police Foundation]]/[[U.S. Department of Justice]] [[Office of Community Oriented Policing Services]] (2017)\n* [http://media.clickorlando.com/document_dev/2016/06/25/Scan16062511570_1466872698408_7194317_ver1.0.pdf Orange County Sheriff's Office - Incident report] ([https://www.webcitation.org/6iZfl4RhY?url=http://media.clickorlando.com/document_dev/2016/06/25/Scan16062511570_1466872698408_7194317